184	#define MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${id}_CRC ${crc_extra}
185	
186	${{array_fields:#define MAVLINK_MSG_${msg_name}_FIELD_${name_upper}_LEN ${array_length}
187	}}
188	
189	#if MAVLINK_COMMAND_24BIT
190	#define MAVLINK_MESSAGE_INFO_${name} { \\
191	    ${id}, \\
192	    "${name}", \\
193	    ${num_fields}, \\
194	    { ${{fields: { "${name}", ${c_print_format}, MAVLINK_TYPE_${type_upper}, ${array_length}, ${wire_offset}, offsetof(mavlink_${name_lower}_t, ${name}) }, \\
195	        }} } \\
196	}
197	#else
198	#define MAVLINK_MESSAGE_INFO_${name} { \\
199	    "${name}", \\
200	    ${num_fields}, \\
201	    { ${{fields: { "${name}", ${c_print_format}, MAVLINK_TYPE_${type_upper}, ${array_length}, ${wire_offset}, offsetof(mavlink_${name_lower}_t, ${name}) }, \\
202	        }} } \\
203	}
204	#endif
205	
206	/**
207	 * @brief Pack a ${name_lower} message
208	 * @param system_id ID of this system
209	 * @param component_id ID of this component (e.g. 200 for IMU)
210	 * @param msg The MAVLink message to compress the data into
211	 *
212	${{arg_fields: * @param ${name} ${units} ${description}
213	}}
214	 * @return length of the message in bytes (excluding serial stream start sign)
215	 */
216	static inline uint16_t mavlink_msg_${name_lower}_pack(uint8_t system_id, uint8_t component_id, mavlink_message_t* msg,
217	                              ${{arg_fields: ${array_const}${type} ${array_prefix}${name},}})
218	{
219	#if MAVLINK_NEED_BYTE_SWAP || !MAVLINK_ALIGNED_FIELDS
220	    char buf[MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_LEN];
221	${{scalar_fields:    _mav_put_${type}(buf, ${wire_offset}, ${putname});
222	}}
223	${{array_fields:    _mav_put_${type}_array(buf, ${wire_offset}, ${name}, ${array_length});
224	}}
225	        memcpy(_MAV_PAYLOAD_NON_CONST(msg), buf, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_LEN);
226	#else
227	    mavlink_${name_lower}_t packet;
228	${{scalar_fields:    packet.${name} = ${putname};
229	}}
230	${{array_fields:    mav_array_memcpy(packet.${name}, ${name}, sizeof(${type})*${array_length});
231	}}
232	        memcpy(_MAV_PAYLOAD_NON_CONST(msg), &packet, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_LEN);
233	#endif
234	
235	    msg->msgid = MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name};
236	    return mavlink_finalize_message(msg, system_id, component_id, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_MIN_LEN, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_LEN, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_CRC);
237	}
238	
239	/**
240	 * @brief Pack a ${name_lower} message
241	 * @param system_id ID of this system
242	 * @param component_id ID of this component (e.g. 200 for IMU)
243	 * @param status MAVLink status structure
244	 * @param msg The MAVLink message to compress the data into
245	 *
246	${{arg_fields: * @param ${name} ${units} ${description}
247	}}
248	 * @return length of the message in bytes (excluding serial stream start sign)
249	 */
250	static inline uint16_t mavlink_msg_${name_lower}_pack_status(uint8_t system_id, uint8_t component_id, mavlink_status_t *_status, mavlink_message_t* msg,
251	                              ${{arg_fields: ${array_const}${type} ${array_prefix}${name},}})
252	{
253	#if MAVLINK_NEED_BYTE_SWAP || !MAVLINK_ALIGNED_FIELDS
254	    char buf[MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_LEN];
255	${{scalar_fields:    _mav_put_${type}(buf, ${wire_offset}, ${putname});
256	}}
257	${{array_fields:    _mav_put_${type}_array(buf, ${wire_offset}, ${name}, ${array_length});
258	}}
259	        memcpy(_MAV_PAYLOAD_NON_CONST(msg), buf, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_LEN);
260	#else
261	    mavlink_${name_lower}_t packet;
262	${{scalar_fields:    packet.${name} = ${putname};
263	}}
264	${{array_fields:    mav_array_memcpy(packet.${name}, ${name}, sizeof(${type})*${array_length});
265	}}
266	        memcpy(_MAV_PAYLOAD_NON_CONST(msg), &packet, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_LEN);
267	#endif
268	
269	    msg->msgid = MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name};
270	#if MAVLINK_CRC_EXTRA
271	    return mavlink_finalize_message_buffer(msg, system_id, component_id, _status, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_MIN_LEN, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_LEN, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_CRC);
272	#else
273	    return mavlink_finalize_message_buffer(msg, system_id, component_id, _status, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_MIN_LEN, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_LEN);
274	#endif
275	}
276	
277	/**
278	 * @brief Pack a ${name_lower} message on a channel
279	 * @param system_id ID of this system
280	 * @param component_id ID of this component (e.g. 200 for IMU)
281	 * @param chan The MAVLink channel this message will be sent over
282	 * @param msg The MAVLink message to compress the data into
283	${{arg_fields: * @param ${name} ${units} ${description}
284	}}
285	 * @return length of the message in bytes (excluding serial stream start sign)
286	 */
287	static inline uint16_t mavlink_msg_${name_lower}_pack_chan(uint8_t system_id, uint8_t component_id, uint8_t chan,
288	                               mavlink_message_t* msg,
289	                                   ${{arg_fields:${array_const}${type} ${array_prefix}${name},}})
290	{
291	#if MAVLINK_NEED_BYTE_SWAP || !MAVLINK_ALIGNED_FIELDS
292	    char buf[MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_LEN];
293	${{scalar_fields:    _mav_put_${type}(buf, ${wire_offset}, ${putname});
294	}}
295	${{array_fields:    _mav_put_${type}_array(buf, ${wire_offset}, ${name}, ${array_length});
296	}}
297	        memcpy(_MAV_PAYLOAD_NON_CONST(msg), buf, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_LEN);
298	#else
299	    mavlink_${name_lower}_t packet;
300	${{scalar_fields:    packet.${name} = ${putname};
301	}}
302	${{array_fields:    mav_array_memcpy(packet.${name}, ${name}, sizeof(${type})*${array_length});
303	}}
304	        memcpy(_MAV_PAYLOAD_NON_CONST(msg), &packet, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_LEN);
305	#endif
306	
307	    msg->msgid = MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name};
308	    return mavlink_finalize_message_chan(msg, system_id, component_id, chan, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_MIN_LEN, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_LEN, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_CRC);
309	}
310	
311	/**
312	 * @brief Encode a ${name_lower} struct
313	 *
314	 * @param system_id ID of this system
315	 * @param component_id ID of this component (e.g. 200 for IMU)
316	 * @param msg The MAVLink message to compress the data into
317	 * @param ${name_lower} C-struct to read the message contents from
318	 */
319	static inline uint16_t mavlink_msg_${name_lower}_encode(uint8_t system_id, uint8_t component_id, mavlink_message_t* msg, const mavlink_${name_lower}_t* ${name_lower})
320	{
321	    return mavlink_msg_${name_lower}_pack(system_id, component_id, msg,${{arg_fields: ${name_lower}->${name},}});
322	}
323	
324	/**
325	 * @brief Encode a ${name_lower} struct on a channel
326	 *
327	 * @param system_id ID of this system
328	 * @param component_id ID of this component (e.g. 200 for IMU)
329	 * @param chan The MAVLink channel this message will be sent over
330	 * @param msg The MAVLink message to compress the data into
331	 * @param ${name_lower} C-struct to read the message contents from
332	 */
333	static inline uint16_t mavlink_msg_${name_lower}_encode_chan(uint8_t system_id, uint8_t component_id, uint8_t chan, mavlink_message_t* msg, const mavlink_${name_lower}_t* ${name_lower})
334	{
335	    return mavlink_msg_${name_lower}_pack_chan(system_id, component_id, chan, msg,${{arg_fields: ${name_lower}->${name},}});
336	}
337	
338	/**
339	 * @brief Encode a ${name_lower} struct with provided status structure
340	 *
341	 * @param system_id ID of this system
342	 * @param component_id ID of this component (e.g. 200 for IMU)
343	 * @param status MAVLink status structure
344	 * @param msg The MAVLink message to compress the data into
345	 * @param ${name_lower} C-struct to read the message contents from
346	 */
347	static inline uint16_t mavlink_msg_${name_lower}_encode_status(uint8_t system_id, uint8_t component_id, mavlink_status_t* _status, mavlink_message_t* msg, const mavlink_${name_lower}_t* ${name_lower})
348	{
349	    return mavlink_msg_${name_lower}_pack_status(system_id, component_id, _status, msg, ${{arg_fields: ${name_lower}->${name},}});
350	}
351	
352	/**
353	 * @brief Send a ${name_lower} message
354	 * @param chan MAVLink channel to send the message
355	 *
356	${{arg_fields: * @param ${name} ${units} ${description}
357	}}
358	 */
359	#ifdef MAVLINK_USE_CONVENIENCE_FUNCTIONS
360	
361	static inline void mavlink_msg_${name_lower}_send(mavlink_channel_t chan,${{arg_fields: ${array_const}${type} ${array_prefix}${name},}})
362	{
363	#if MAVLINK_NEED_BYTE_SWAP || !MAVLINK_ALIGNED_FIELDS
364	    char buf[MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_LEN];
365	${{scalar_fields:    _mav_put_${type}(buf, ${wire_offset}, ${putname});
366	}}
367	${{array_fields:    _mav_put_${type}_array(buf, ${wire_offset}, ${name}, ${array_length});
368	}}
369	    _mav_finalize_message_chan_send(chan, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}, buf, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_MIN_LEN, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_LEN, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_CRC);
370	#else
371	    mavlink_${name_lower}_t packet;
372	${{scalar_fields:    packet.${name} = ${putname};
373	}}
374	${{array_fields:    mav_array_memcpy(packet.${name}, ${name}, sizeof(${type})*${array_length});
375	}}
376	    _mav_finalize_message_chan_send(chan, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}, (const char *)&packet, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_MIN_LEN, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_LEN, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_CRC);
377	#endif
378	}
379	
380	/**
381	 * @brief Send a ${name_lower} message
382	 * @param chan MAVLink channel to send the message
383	 * @param struct The MAVLink struct to serialize
384	 */
385	static inline void mavlink_msg_${name_lower}_send_struct(mavlink_channel_t chan, const mavlink_${name_lower}_t* ${name_lower})
386	{
387	#if MAVLINK_NEED_BYTE_SWAP || !MAVLINK_ALIGNED_FIELDS
388	    mavlink_msg_${name_lower}_send(chan,${{arg_fields: ${name_lower}->${name},}});
389	#else
390	    _mav_finalize_message_chan_send(chan, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}, (const char *)${name_lower}, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_MIN_LEN, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_LEN, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_CRC);
391	#endif
392	}
393	
394	#if MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_LEN <= MAVLINK_MAX_PAYLOAD_LEN
395	/*
396	  This variant of _send() can be used to save stack space by re-using
397	  memory from the receive buffer.  The caller provides a
398	  mavlink_message_t which is the size of a full mavlink message. This
399	  is usually the receive buffer for the channel, and allows a reply to an
400	  incoming message with minimum stack space usage.
401	 */
402	static inline void mavlink_msg_${name_lower}_send_buf(mavlink_message_t *msgbuf, mavlink_channel_t chan, ${{arg_fields: ${array_const}${type} ${array_prefix}${name},}})
403	{
404	#if MAVLINK_NEED_BYTE_SWAP || !MAVLINK_ALIGNED_FIELDS
405	    char *buf = (char *)msgbuf;
406	${{scalar_fields:    _mav_put_${type}(buf, ${wire_offset}, ${putname});
407	}}
408	${{array_fields:    _mav_put_${type}_array(buf, ${wire_offset}, ${name}, ${array_length});
409	}}
410	    _mav_finalize_message_chan_send(chan, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}, buf, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_MIN_LEN, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_LEN, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_CRC);
411	#else
412	    mavlink_${name_lower}_t *packet = (mavlink_${name_lower}_t *)msgbuf;
413	${{scalar_fields:    packet->${name} = ${putname};
414	}}
415	${{array_fields:    mav_array_memcpy(packet->${name}, ${name}, sizeof(${type})*${array_length});
416	}}
417	    _mav_finalize_message_chan_send(chan, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}, (const char *)packet, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_MIN_LEN, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_LEN, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_CRC);
418	#endif
419	}
420	#endif
421	
422	#endif
423	
424	// MESSAGE ${name} UNPACKING
425	
426	${{fields:
427	/**
428	 * @brief Get field ${name} from ${name_lower} message
429	 *
430	 * @return ${units} ${description}
431	 */
432	static inline ${return_type} mavlink_msg_${name_lower}_get_${name}(const mavlink_message_t* msg${get_arg})
433	{
434	    return _MAV_RETURN_${type}${array_tag}(msg, ${array_return_arg} ${wire_offset});
435	}
436	}}
437	
438	/**
439	 * @brief Decode a ${name_lower} message into a struct
440	 *
441	 * @param msg The message to decode
442	 * @param ${name_lower} C-struct to decode the message contents into
443	 */
444	static inline void mavlink_msg_${name_lower}_decode(const mavlink_message_t* msg, mavlink_${name_lower}_t* ${name_lower})
445	{
446	#if MAVLINK_NEED_BYTE_SWAP || !MAVLINK_ALIGNED_FIELDS
447	${{ordered_fields:    ${decode_left}mavlink_msg_${name_lower}_get_${name}(msg${decode_right});
448	}}
449	#else
450	        uint8_t len = msg->len < MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_LEN? msg->len : MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_LEN;
451	        memset(${name_lower}, 0, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_LEN);
452	    memcpy(${name_lower}, _MAV_PAYLOAD(msg), len);
453	#endif
454	}
455	''', m)
456	    f.close()

463	/** @file
464	 *    @brief MAVLink comm protocol testsuite generated from ${basename}.xml
465	 *    @see https://mavlink.io/en/
466	 */
467	#pragma once
468	#ifndef ${basename_upper}_TESTSUITE_H
469	#define ${basename_upper}_TESTSUITE_H
470	
471	#ifdef __cplusplus
472	extern "C" {
473	#endif
474	
475	#ifndef MAVLINK_TEST_ALL
476	#define MAVLINK_TEST_ALL
477	${{include_list:static void mavlink_test_${base}(uint8_t, uint8_t, mavlink_message_t *last_msg);
478	}}
479	static void mavlink_test_${basename}(uint8_t, uint8_t, mavlink_message_t *last_msg);
480	
481	static void mavlink_test_all(uint8_t system_id, uint8_t component_id, mavlink_message_t *last_msg)
482	{
483	${{include_list:    mavlink_test_${base}(system_id, component_id, last_msg);
484	}}
485	    mavlink_test_${basename}(system_id, component_id, last_msg);
486	}
487	#endif
488	
489	${{include_list:#include "../${base}/testsuite.h"
490	}}
491	
492	${{message:
493	static void mavlink_test_${name_lower}(uint8_t system_id, uint8_t component_id, mavlink_message_t *last_msg)
494	{
495	#ifdef MAVLINK_STATUS_FLAG_OUT_MAVLINK1
496	    mavlink_status_t *status = mavlink_get_channel_status(MAVLINK_COMM_0);
497	        if ((status->flags & MAVLINK_STATUS_FLAG_OUT_MAVLINK1) && MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name} >= 256) {
498	            return;
499	        }
500	#endif
501	    mavlink_message_t msg;
502	        uint8_t buffer[MAVLINK_MAX_PACKET_LEN];
503	        uint16_t i;
504	    mavlink_${name_lower}_t packet_in = {
505	        ${{ordered_fields:${c_test_value},}}
506	    };
507	    mavlink_${name_lower}_t packet1, packet2;
508	        memset(&packet1, 0, sizeof(packet1));
509	        ${{scalar_fields:packet1.${name} = packet_in.${name};
510	        }}
511	        ${{array_fields:mav_array_memcpy(packet1.${name}, packet_in.${name}, sizeof(${type})*${array_length});
512	        }}
513	#ifdef MAVLINK_STATUS_FLAG_OUT_MAVLINK1
514	        if (status->flags & MAVLINK_STATUS_FLAG_OUT_MAVLINK1) {
515	           // cope with extensions
516	           memset(MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_MIN_LEN + (char *)&packet1, 0, sizeof(packet1)-MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}_MIN_LEN);
517	        }
518	#endif
519	        memset(&packet2, 0, sizeof(packet2));
520	    mavlink_msg_${name_lower}_encode(system_id, component_id, &msg, &packet1);
521	    mavlink_msg_${name_lower}_decode(&msg, &packet2);
522	        MAVLINK_ASSERT(memcmp(&packet1, &packet2, sizeof(packet1)) == 0);
523	
524	        memset(&packet2, 0, sizeof(packet2));
525	    mavlink_msg_${name_lower}_pack(system_id, component_id, &msg ${{arg_fields:, packet1.${name} }});
526	    mavlink_msg_${name_lower}_decode(&msg, &packet2);
527	        MAVLINK_ASSERT(memcmp(&packet1, &packet2, sizeof(packet1)) == 0);
528	
529	        memset(&packet2, 0, sizeof(packet2));
530	    mavlink_msg_${name_lower}_pack_chan(system_id, component_id, MAVLINK_COMM_0, &msg ${{arg_fields:, packet1.${name} }});
531	    mavlink_msg_${name_lower}_decode(&msg, &packet2);
532	        MAVLINK_ASSERT(memcmp(&packet1, &packet2, sizeof(packet1)) == 0);
533	
534	        memset(&packet2, 0, sizeof(packet2));
535	        mavlink_msg_to_send_buffer(buffer, &msg);
536	        for (i=0; i<mavlink_msg_get_send_buffer_length(&msg); i++) {
537	            comm_send_ch(MAVLINK_COMM_0, buffer[i]);
538	        }
539	    mavlink_msg_${name_lower}_decode(last_msg, &packet2);
540	        MAVLINK_ASSERT(memcmp(&packet1, &packet2, sizeof(packet1)) == 0);
541	        
542	        memset(&packet2, 0, sizeof(packet2));
543	    mavlink_msg_${name_lower}_send(MAVLINK_COMM_1 ${{arg_fields:, packet1.${name} }});
544	    mavlink_msg_${name_lower}_decode(last_msg, &packet2);
545	        MAVLINK_ASSERT(memcmp(&packet1, &packet2, sizeof(packet1)) == 0);
546	
547	#ifdef MAVLINK_HAVE_GET_MESSAGE_INFO
548	    MAVLINK_ASSERT(mavlink_get_message_info_by_name("${name}") != NULL);
549	    MAVLINK_ASSERT(mavlink_get_message_info_by_id(MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}) != NULL);
550	#endif
551	}
552	}}
553	
554	static void mavlink_test_${basename}(uint8_t system_id, uint8_t component_id, mavlink_message_t *last_msg)
555	{
556	${{message:    mavlink_test_${name_lower}(system_id, component_id, last_msg);
557	}}
558	}
559	
560	#ifdef __cplusplus
561	}
562	#endif // __cplusplus
563	#endif // ${basename_upper}_TESTSUITE_H
564	''', xml)
565

523	
524	        memset(&packet2, 0, sizeof(packet2));
525	    mavlink_msg_${name_lower}_pack(system_id, component_id, &msg ${{arg_fields:, packet1.${name} }});
526	    mavlink_msg_${name_lower}_decode(&msg, &packet2);
527	        MAVLINK_ASSERT(memcmp(&packet1, &packet2, sizeof(packet1)) == 0);
528	
529	        memset(&packet2, 0, sizeof(packet2));
530	    mavlink_msg_${name_lower}_pack_chan(system_id, component_id, MAVLINK_COMM_0, &msg ${{arg_fields:, packet1.${name} }});
531	    mavlink_msg_${name_lower}_decode(&msg, &packet2);
532	        MAVLINK_ASSERT(memcmp(&packet1, &packet2, sizeof(packet1)) == 0);
533	
534	        memset(&packet2, 0, sizeof(packet2));
535	        mavlink_msg_to_send_buffer(buffer, &msg);
536	        for (i=0; i<mavlink_msg_get_send_buffer_length(&msg); i++) {
537	            comm_send_ch(MAVLINK_COMM_0, buffer[i]);
538	        }
539	    mavlink_msg_${name_lower}_decode(last_msg, &packet2);
540	        MAVLINK_ASSERT(memcmp(&packet1, &packet2, sizeof(packet1)) == 0);
541	        
542	        memset(&packet2, 0, sizeof(packet2));
543	    mavlink_msg_${name_lower}_send(MAVLINK_COMM_1 ${{arg_fields:, packet1.${name} }});
544	    mavlink_msg_${name_lower}_decode(last_msg, &packet2);
545	        MAVLINK_ASSERT(memcmp(&packet1, &packet2, sizeof(packet1)) == 0);
546	
547	#ifdef MAVLINK_HAVE_GET_MESSAGE_INFO
548	    MAVLINK_ASSERT(mavlink_get_message_info_by_name("${name}") != NULL);
549	    MAVLINK_ASSERT(mavlink_get_message_info_by_id(MAVLINK_MSG_ID_${name}) != NULL);
550	#endif
551	}
552	}}
553	
554	static void mavlink_test_${basename}(uint8_t system_id, uint8_t component_id, mavlink_message_t *last_msg)
555	{
556	${{message:    mavlink_test_${name_lower}(system_id, component_id, last_msg);
557	}}
558	}
559	
560	#ifdef __cplusplus
561	}
562	#endif // __cplusplus
563	#endif // ${basename_upper}_TESTSUITE_H
564	''', xml)

>> Issue: [B815:write] os.write
   Severity: High   Confidence: Medium
   Location: /home/blue/PyPIAgent/Dataset/study/unzip_benign/pymavlink-2.4.43/pymavlink-2.4.43/generator/mavgen_java.py:62
   More Info: https://bandit.readthedocs.io/en/latest/plugins/b815_write.html
61	    f = open(os.path.join(directory, "CRC.java"), mode='w')
62	    t.write(f,'''
63	/* AUTO-GENERATED FILE.  DO NOT MODIFY.
64	 *
65	 * This class was automatically generated by the
66	 * java mavlink generator tool. It should not be modified by hand.
67	 */
68	
69	package com.MAVLink.${basename};
70	
71	import java.util.HashMap;
72	import java.util.Map;
73	
74	/**
75	 * CRC-16/MCRF4XX calculation for MAVlink messages. The checksum must be
76	 * initialized, updated with which field of the message, and then finished with
77	 * the message id.
78	 *
79	 */
80	public class CRC {
81	    private static final Map<Integer, Integer> MAVLINK_MESSAGE_CRCS;
82	    private static final int CRC_INIT_VALUE = 0xffff;
83	    private int crcValue;
84	
85	    static {
86	        MAVLINK_MESSAGE_CRCS = new HashMap<>();
87	        ${message_crcs_array}
88	    }
89	
90	    /**
91	     * Accumulate the CRC by adding one char at a time.
92	     *
93	     * The checksum function adds the hash of one char at a time to the 16 bit
94	     * checksum (uint16_t).
95	     *
96	     * @param data new char to hash
97	     **/
98	    public void update_checksum(int data) {
99	        data = data & 0xff; //cast because we want an unsigned type
100	        int tmp = data ^ (crcValue & 0xff);
101	        tmp ^= (tmp << 4) & 0xff;
102	        crcValue = ((crcValue >> 8) & 0xff) ^ (tmp << 8) ^ (tmp << 3) ^ ((tmp >> 4) & 0xf);
103	    }
104	
105	    /**
106	     * Finish the CRC calculation of a message, by running the CRC with the
107	     * Magic Byte.
108	     *
109	     * @param msgid The message id number
110	     * @return boolean True if the checksum was successfully finished. Otherwise false
111	     */
112	    public boolean finish_checksum(int msgid) {
113	        if (MAVLINK_MESSAGE_CRCS.containsKey(msgid)) {
114	            update_checksum(MAVLINK_MESSAGE_CRCS.get(msgid));
115	            return true;
116	        }
117	        return false;
118	    }
119	
120	    /**
121	     * Initialize the buffer for the CRC16/MCRF4XX
122	     */
123	    public void start_checksum() {
124	        crcValue = CRC_INIT_VALUE;
125	    }
126	
127	    public int getMSB() {
128	        return ((crcValue >> 8) & 0xff);
129	    }
130	
131	    public int getLSB() {
132	        return (crcValue & 0xff);
133	    }
134	
135	    public CRC() {
136	        start_checksum();
137	    }
138	
139	}
140	        ''',xml)

299	/* AUTO-GENERATED FILE.  DO NOT MODIFY.
300	 *
301	 * This class was automatically generated by the
302	 * java mavlink generator tool. It should not be modified by hand.
303	 */
304	
305	package com.MAVLink;
306	
307	import java.io.Serializable;
308	import com.MAVLink.Messages.MAVLinkPayload;
309	import com.MAVLink.Messages.MAVLinkMessage;
310	import com.MAVLink.${basename}.CRC;
311	
312	${importString}
313	
314	/**
315	 * Common interface for all MAVLink Messages
316	 * Packet Anatomy
317	 * This is the anatomy of one packet. It is inspired by the CAN and SAE AS-4 standards.
318	 *
319	 * MAVLink 1 Packet Format
320	 *
321	 * Byte Index  Content              Value       Explanation
322	 * 0            Packet start sign  v1.0: 0xFE   Indicates the start of a new packet.  (v0.9: 0x55; v1.0: 0xFE; v2.0 0xFD)
323	 * 1            Payload length      0 - 255     Indicates length of the following payload.
324	 * 2            Packet sequence     0 - 255     Each component counts up its send sequence. Allows to detect packet loss
325	 * 3            System ID           1 - 255     ID of the SENDING system. Allows to differentiate different MAVs on the same network.
326	 * 4            Component ID        0 - 255     ID of the SENDING component. Allows to differentiate different components of the same system, e.g. the IMU and the autopilot.
327	 * 5            Message ID          0 - 255     ID of the message - the id defines what the payload means and how it should be correctly decoded.
328	 * 6 to (n+6)   Payload             0 - 255     Data of the message, depends on the message id.
329	 * (n+7)to(n+8) Checksum (low byte, high byte)  CRC16/MCRF4XX hash, excluding packet start sign, so bytes 1..(n+6) Note: The checksum also includes MAVLINK_CRC_EXTRA (Number computed from message fields. Protects the packet from decoding a different version of the same packet but with different variables).
330	 *
331	 * The checksum is the CRC16/MCRF4XX. Please see the MAVLink source code for a documented C-implementation of it. LINK TO CHECKSUM
332	 * The minimum packet length is 8 bytes for acknowledgement packets without payload
333	 * The maximum packet length is 263 bytes for full payload
334	 *
335	 *
336	 * MAVLink 2 Packet Format
337	 *
338	 * Byte Index     Content             Value              Explanation
339	 * 0              Packet start sign  v2.0: 0xFD          Indicates the start of a new packet.  (v0.9: 0x55; v1.0: 0xFE; v2.0 0xFD)
340	 * 1              Payload length      0 - 255            Indicates length of the following payload.
341	 * 2              Incompatible Flags  0 - 255            Flags that must be understood
342	 * 3              Compatible Flags    0 - 255            Flags that can be ignored if not understood
343	 * 4              Packet sequence     0 - 255            Each component counts up its send sequence. Allows to detect packet loss
344	 * 5              System ID           1 - 255            ID of the SENDING system. Allows to differentiate different MAVs on the same network.
345	 * 6              Component ID        0 - 255            ID of the SENDING component. Allows to differentiate different components of the same system, e.g. the IMU and the autopilot.
346	 * 7 to 9         Message ID          0 - 16777216       ID of the message - the id defines what the payload means and how it should be correctly decoded.
347	 * 10             Target System ID    1 - 255            (OPTIONAL) ID of the TARGET system. Only used for point-to-point mode
348	 * 11             Target Component ID 0 - 255            (OPTIONAL) ID of the TARGET component. Only used for point-to-point mode
349	 * 12 to (n+12)   Payload             0 - 255            Data of the message, depends on the message id.
350	 * (n+13)to(n+14) Checksum (low byte, high byte)         CRC16/MCRF4XX hash, excluding packet start sign, so bytes 1..(n+6) Note: The checksum also includes MAVLINK_CRC_EXTRA (Number computed from message fields. Protects the packet from decoding a different version of the same packet but with different variables).
351	 * (n+15)to(n+27) Signature (typeid, timestamp, sha256)  (OPTIONAL) Signature which allows ensuring that the link is tamper-proof; 13 bytes containing typeid (1 byte), timestamp (6 bytes), and last 6 bytes of SHA256 hash
352	 *
353	 * The signature is a combination of a typeid, timestamp, and SHA256 hash.
354	 * OPTIONAL fields mean that, if they are not used, they do not exist in the MAVLink frame at all. Typically target sysid and target compid are not used, and signature is only used if signing is set up between both ends.
355	 *
356	 * @see <a href="https://mavlink.io">mavlink.io</a> for more documentation on the MAVLink protocol
357	 */
358	public class MAVLinkPacket implements Serializable {
359	    private static final long serialVersionUID = 2095947771227815314L;
360	
361	    public static final int MAVLINK_STX_MAVLINK1 = 0xFE; // 254
362	    public static final int MAVLINK_STX_MAVLINK2 = 0xFD; // 253
363	    public static final int MAVLINK1_HEADER_LEN = 6;
364	    public static final int MAVLINK2_HEADER_LEN = 10;
365	    public static final int MAVLINK1_NONPAYLOAD_LEN = MAVLINK1_HEADER_LEN + 2;
366	    public static final int MAVLINK2_NONPAYLOAD_LEN = MAVLINK2_HEADER_LEN + 2;
367	
368	    static final boolean V = false;
369	    static void logv(String str) {
370	        if(V) System.out.println(String.format("MAVLinkPacket: %s", str));
371	    }
372	
373	    /**
374	     * Payload length
375	     */
376	    public final int len;
377	
378	    /**
379	     * Message sequence
380	     */
381	    public int seq;
382	
383	    /**
384	     * ID of the SENDING system. Allows to differentiate different MAVs on the
385	     * same network.
386	     */
387	    public int sysid;
388	
389	    /**
390	     * ID of the SENDING component. Allows to differentiate different components
391	     * of the same system, e.g. the IMU and the autopilot.
392	     */
393	    public int compid;
394	
395	    /**
396	     * ID of the message - the id defines what the payload means and how it
397	     * should be correctly decoded.
398	     */
399	    public int msgid;
400	
401	    /**
402	     * Data of the message, depends on the message id.
403	     */
404	    public MAVLinkPayload payload;
405	
406	    /**
407	    * CRC-16/MCRF4XX hash, excluding packet start sign, so bytes 1..(n+HEADER-LENGTH)
408	    * Note: The checksum also includes MAVLINK_CRC_EXTRA (Number computed from
409	    * message fields. Protects the packet from decoding a different version of
410	    * the same packet but with different variables).
411	    */
412	    public CRC crc;
413	
414	    // MAVLink 2.0 fields
415	
416	    /**
417	     * Flag to indicate which MAVLink version this packet is
418	     */
419	    public boolean isMavlink2;
420	
421	    /**
422	     * Flags that must be understood
423	     */
424	    public int incompatFlags;
425	
426	    /**
427	     * Flags that can be ignored if not understood
428	     */
429	    public int compatFlags;
430	
431	    public MAVLinkPacket(int payloadLength) {
432	        this(payloadLength, false);
433	    }
434	
435	    public MAVLinkPacket(final int payloadLength, final boolean isMavlink2) {
436	        len = payloadLength;
437	        payload = new MAVLinkPayload();
438	        this.isMavlink2 = isMavlink2;
439	    }
440	
441	    /**
442	     * Check if the size of the Payload is equal to the "len" byte
443	     */
444	    public boolean payloadIsFilled() {
445	        return payload.size() >= len;
446	    }
447	
448	    /**
449	     * Update CRC for this packet.
450	     * @return boolean True if the CRC was successfully updated. Otherwise false
451	     */
452	    public boolean generateCRC(final int payloadSize) {
453	        if (crc == null) {
454	            crc = new CRC();
455	        } else {
456	            crc.start_checksum();
457	        }
458	
459	        if (isMavlink2) {
460	            crc.update_checksum(payloadSize);
461	            crc.update_checksum(incompatFlags);
462	            crc.update_checksum(compatFlags);
463	            crc.update_checksum(seq);
464	            crc.update_checksum(sysid);
465	            crc.update_checksum(compid);
466	            crc.update_checksum(msgid);
467	            crc.update_checksum(msgid >>> 8);
468	            crc.update_checksum(msgid >>> 16);
469	        } else {
470	            crc.update_checksum(payloadSize);
471	            crc.update_checksum(seq);
472	            crc.update_checksum(sysid);
473	            crc.update_checksum(compid);
474	            crc.update_checksum(msgid);
475	        }
476	
477	        payload.resetIndex();
478	
479	        for (int i = 0; i < payloadSize; i++) {
480	            crc.update_checksum(payload.getByte());
481	        }
482	        return crc.finish_checksum(msgid);
483	    }
484	
485	    /**
486	     * Return length of actual data after trimming zeros at the end.
487	     * @param payload
488	     * @return minimum length of valid data
489	     */
490	    private int mavTrimPayload(final byte[] payload)
491	    {
492	        int length = payload.length;
493	        while (length > 1 && payload[length-1] == 0) {
494	            length--;
495	        }
496	        return length;
497	    }
498	
499	    /**
500	     * Encode this packet for transmission.
501	     *
502	     * @return Array with bytes to be transmitted
503	     */
504	    public byte[] encodePacket() {
505	        final int bufLen;
506	        final int payloadSize;
507	
508	        if (isMavlink2) {
509	            payloadSize = mavTrimPayload(payload.payload.array());
510	            bufLen = MAVLINK2_HEADER_LEN + payloadSize + 2;
511	        } else {
512	            payloadSize = payload.size();
513	            bufLen = MAVLINK1_HEADER_LEN + payloadSize + 2;
514	
515	        }
516	        byte[] buffer = new byte[bufLen];
517	
518	        int i = 0;
519	        if (isMavlink2) {
520	            buffer[i++] = (byte) MAVLINK_STX_MAVLINK2;
521	            buffer[i++] = (byte) payloadSize;
522	            buffer[i++] = (byte) incompatFlags;
523	            buffer[i++] = (byte) compatFlags;
524	            buffer[i++] = (byte) seq;
525	            buffer[i++] = (byte) sysid;
526	            buffer[i++] = (byte) compid;
527	            buffer[i++] = (byte) (msgid & 0XFF);
528	            buffer[i++] = (byte) ((msgid >>> 8) & 0XFF);
529	            buffer[i++] = (byte) ((msgid >>> 16) & 0XFF);
530	        } else {
531	            buffer[i++] = (byte) MAVLINK_STX_MAVLINK1;
532	            buffer[i++] = (byte) payloadSize;
533	            buffer[i++] = (byte) seq;
534	            buffer[i++] = (byte) sysid;
535	            buffer[i++] = (byte) compid;
536	            buffer[i++] = (byte) msgid;
537	        }
538	
539	        for (int j = 0; j < payloadSize; ++j) {
540	            buffer[i++] = payload.payload.get(j);
541	        }
542	
543	        generateCRC(payloadSize);
544	        buffer[i++] = (byte) (crc.getLSB());
545	        buffer[i++] = (byte) (crc.getMSB());
546	
547	        logv(String.format("encode: isMavlink2=%s msgid=%d", isMavlink2, msgid));
548	
549	        return buffer;
550	    }

354	 * OPTIONAL fields mean that, if they are not used, they do not exist in the MAVLink frame at all. Typically target sysid and target compid are not used, and signature is only used if signing is set up between both ends.
355	 *
356	 * @see <a href="https://mavlink.io">mavlink.io</a> for more documentation on the MAVLink protocol
357	 */
358	public class MAVLinkPacket implements Serializable {
359	    private static final long serialVersionUID = 2095947771227815314L;
360	
361	    public static final int MAVLINK_STX_MAVLINK1 = 0xFE; // 254
362	    public static final int MAVLINK_STX_MAVLINK2 = 0xFD; // 253
363	    public static final int MAVLINK1_HEADER_LEN = 6;
364	    public static final int MAVLINK2_HEADER_LEN = 10;
365	    public static final int MAVLINK1_NONPAYLOAD_LEN = MAVLINK1_HEADER_LEN + 2;
366	    public static final int MAVLINK2_NONPAYLOAD_LEN = MAVLINK2_HEADER_LEN + 2;
367	
368	    static final boolean V = false;
369	    static void logv(String str) {
370	        if(V) System.out.println(String.format("MAVLinkPacket: %s", str));
371	    }
372	
373	    /**
374	     * Payload length
375	     */
376	    public final int len;
377	
378	    /**
379	     * Message sequence
380	     */
381	    public int seq;
382	
383	    /**
384	     * ID of the SENDING system. Allows to differentiate different MAVs on the
385	     * same network.
386	     */
387	    public int sysid;
388	
389	    /**
390	     * ID of the SENDING component. Allows to differentiate different components
391	     * of the same system, e.g. the IMU and the autopilot.
392	     */
393	    public int compid;
394	
395	    /**
396	     * ID of the message - the id defines what the payload means and how it
397	     * should be correctly decoded.
398	     */
399	    public int msgid;
400	
401	    /**
402	     * Data of the message, depends on the message id.
403	     */
404	    public MAVLinkPayload payload;
405	
406	    /**
407	    * CRC-16/MCRF4XX hash, excluding packet start sign, so bytes 1..(n+HEADER-LENGTH)
408	    * Note: The checksum also includes MAVLINK_CRC_EXTRA (Number computed from
409	    * message fields. Protects the packet from decoding a different version of
410	    * the same packet but with different variables).
411	    */
412	    public CRC crc;
413	
414	    // MAVLink 2.0 fields
415	
416	    /**
417	     * Flag to indicate which MAVLink version this packet is
418	     */
419	    public boolean isMavlink2;
420	
421	    /**
422	     * Flags that must be understood
423	     */
424	    public int incompatFlags;
425	
426	    /**
427	     * Flags that can be ignored if not understood
428	     */
429	    public int compatFlags;
430	
431	    public MAVLinkPacket(int payloadLength) {
432	        this(payloadLength, false);
433	    }
434	
435	    public MAVLinkPacket(final int payloadLength, final boolean isMavlink2) {
436	        len = payloadLength;
437	        payload = new MAVLinkPayload();
438	        this.isMavlink2 = isMavlink2;
439	    }
440	
441	    /**
442	     * Check if the size of the Payload is equal to the "len" byte
443	     */
444	    public boolean payloadIsFilled() {
445	        return payload.size() >= len;
446	    }
447	
448	    /**
449	     * Update CRC for this packet.
450	     * @return boolean True if the CRC was successfully updated. Otherwise false
451	     */
452	    public boolean generateCRC(final int payloadSize) {
453	        if (crc == null) {
454	            crc = new CRC();
455	        } else {
456	            crc.start_checksum();
457	        }
458	
459	        if (isMavlink2) {
460	            crc.update_checksum(payloadSize);
461	            crc.update_checksum(incompatFlags);
462	            crc.update_checksum(compatFlags);
463	            crc.update_checksum(seq);
464	            crc.update_checksum(sysid);
465	            crc.update_checksum(compid);
466	            crc.update_checksum(msgid);
467	            crc.update_checksum(msgid >>> 8);
468	            crc.update_checksum(msgid >>> 16);
469	        } else {
470	            crc.update_checksum(payloadSize);
471	            crc.update_checksum(seq);
472	            crc.update_checksum(sysid);
473	            crc.update_checksum(compid);
474	            crc.update_checksum(msgid);
475	        }
476	
477	        payload.resetIndex();
478	
479	        for (int i = 0; i < payloadSize; i++) {
480	            crc.update_checksum(payload.getByte());
481	        }
482	        return crc.finish_checksum(msgid);
483	    }
484	
485	    /**
486	     * Return length of actual data after trimming zeros at the end.
487	     * @param payload
488	     * @return minimum length of valid data
489	     */
490	    private int mavTrimPayload(final byte[] payload)
491	    {
492	        int length = payload.length;
493	        while (length > 1 && payload[length-1] == 0) {
494	            length--;
495	        }
496	        return length;
497	    }
498	
499	    /**
500	     * Encode this packet for transmission.
501	     *
502	     * @return Array with bytes to be transmitted
503	     */
504	    public byte[] encodePacket() {
505	        final int bufLen;
506	        final int payloadSize;
507	
508	        if (isMavlink2) {
509	            payloadSize = mavTrimPayload(payload.payload.array());
510	            bufLen = MAVLINK2_HEADER_LEN + payloadSize + 2;
511	        } else {
512	            payloadSize = payload.size();
513	            bufLen = MAVLINK1_HEADER_LEN + payloadSize + 2;
514	
515	        }
516	        byte[] buffer = new byte[bufLen];
517	
518	        int i = 0;
519	        if (isMavlink2) {
520	            buffer[i++] = (byte) MAVLINK_STX_MAVLINK2;
521	            buffer[i++] = (byte) payloadSize;
522	            buffer[i++] = (byte) incompatFlags;
523	            buffer[i++] = (byte) compatFlags;
524	            buffer[i++] = (byte) seq;
525	            buffer[i++] = (byte) sysid;
526	            buffer[i++] = (byte) compid;
527	            buffer[i++] = (byte) (msgid & 0XFF);
528	            buffer[i++] = (byte) ((msgid >>> 8) & 0XFF);
529	            buffer[i++] = (byte) ((msgid >>> 16) & 0XFF);
530	        } else {
531	            buffer[i++] = (byte) MAVLINK_STX_MAVLINK1;
532	            buffer[i++] = (byte) payloadSize;
533	            buffer[i++] = (byte) seq;
534	            buffer[i++] = (byte) sysid;
535	            buffer[i++] = (byte) compid;
536	            buffer[i++] = (byte) msgid;
537	        }
538	
539	        for (int j = 0; j < payloadSize; ++j) {
540	            buffer[i++] = payload.payload.get(j);
541	        }
542	
543	        generateCRC(payloadSize);
544	        buffer[i++] = (byte) (crc.getLSB());
545	        buffer[i++] = (byte) (crc.getMSB());
546	
547	        logv(String.format("encode: isMavlink2=%s msgid=%d", isMavlink2, msgid));
548	
549	        return buffer;
550	    }
551	        ''', xml_list[0])
552

54	
55	    var bytes = buffer;
56	    var crcOUT = crcIN ===  undefined ? 0xffff : crcIN;
57	    _.each(bytes, function(e) {
58	        var tmp = e ^ (crcOUT & 0xff);
59	        tmp = (tmp ^ (tmp << 4)) & 0xff;

132	// Convenience setter to facilitate turning the unpacked array of data into member properties
133	${MAVHEAD}.message.prototype.set = function(args,verbose) {
134	// inspect
135	    _.each(this.fieldnames, function(e, i) {
136	        var num = parseInt(i,10);
137	        if (this.hasOwnProperty(e) && isNaN(num)  ){ // asking for an attribute that's non-numeric is ok unless its already an attribute we have
138	            if ( verbose >= 1) { console.log("WARNING, overwriting an existing property is DANGEROUS:"+e+" ==>"+i+"==>"+args[i]+" -> "+JSON.stringify(this)); }

148	// trying to be the same-ish as the python function of the same name
149	${MAVHEAD}.message.prototype.sign_packet = function( mav) {
150	    var crypto= require('crypto');
151	    var h =  crypto.createHash('sha256');
152	
153	    //mav.signing.timestamp is a 48bit number, or 6 bytes.
154	
155	        // due to js not being able to shift numbers  more than 32, we'll use this instead.. 
156	        // js stores all its numbers as a 64bit float with 53 bits of mantissa, so have room for 48 ok. 
157	        // positive shifts left, negative shifts right
158	        function shift(number, shift) { 
159	            return number * Math.pow(2, shift); 
160	        } 
161	
162	    var thigh = shift(mav.signing.timestamp,-32) // 2 bytes from the top, shifted right by 32 bits
163	    var tlow  = (mav.signing.timestamp & 0xfffffff )  // 4 bytes from the bottom
164	
165	    // I means unsigned 4bytes, H means unsigned 2 bytes
166	    // first add the linkid(1 byte) and timestamp(6 bytes) that start the signature
167	    this._msgbuf = this._msgbuf.concat(jspack.Pack('<BIH', [mav.signing.link_id, tlow, thigh  ] ) );
168	 
169	    h.update(mav.signing.secret_key); // secret is already a Buffer
170	    h.update(new Buffer.from(this._msgbuf));
171	    var hashDigest = h.digest();
172	    sig = hashDigest.slice(0,6)
173	    this._msgbuf  = this._msgbuf.concat( ... sig ); 
174	
175	    mav.signing.timestamp += 1
176	} 
177

383	// Special mavlink message to capture malformed data packets for debugging
384	${MAVHEAD}.messages.bad_data = function(data, reason) {
385	    this._id = ${MAVHEAD}.MAVLINK_MSG_ID_BAD_DATA;
386	    this._data = data;
387	    this._reason = reason;
388	    this._msgbuf = data;
389	}
390	${MAVHEAD}.messages.bad_data.prototype = new ${MAVHEAD}.message;
391	
392	//  MAVLink signing state class
393	MAVLinkSigning = function MAVLinkSigning(object){ 
394	        this.secret_key = new Buffer.from([]) ; //new Buffer.from([ 42, 42, 42, 42, 42, 42, 42, 42, 42, 42, 42, 42, 42, 42, 42, 42, 42, 42, 42, 42, 42, 42, 42, 42, 42, 42, 42, 42, 42, 42, 42, 42 ]) // secret key must be a Buffer obj of 32 length 
395	        this.timestamp = 1 
396	        this.link_id = 0 
397	        this.sign_outgoing = false // todo false this 
398	        this.allow_unsigned_callback = undefined 
399	        this.stream_timestamps = {} 
400	        this.sig_count = 0 
401	        this.badsig_count = 0 
402	        this.goodsig_count = 0 
403	        this.unsigned_count = 0 
404	        this.reject_count = 0 
405	} 
406	
407	/* MAVLink protocol handling class */
408	${MAVPROCESSOR} = function(logger, srcSystem, srcComponent) {
409	
410	    this.logger = logger;
411	
412	    this.seq = 0;
413	    this.buf = new Buffer.from([]);
414	    this.bufInError = new Buffer.from([]);
415	   
416	    this.srcSystem = (typeof srcSystem === 'undefined') ? 0 : srcSystem;
417	    this.srcComponent =  (typeof srcComponent === 'undefined') ? 0 : srcComponent;
418	
419	    this.have_prefix_error = false;
420	
421	    // The first packet we expect is a valid header, 6 bytes.
422	    this.protocol_marker = ${PROTOCOL_MARKER};   
423	    this.expected_length = ${MAVHEAD}.HEADER_LEN;
424	    this.little_endian = true;
425	
426	    this.crc_extra = true;
427	    this.sort_fields = true;
428	    this.total_packets_sent = 0;
429	    this.total_bytes_sent = 0;
430	    this.total_packets_received = 0;
431	    this.total_bytes_received = 0;
432	    this.total_receive_errors = 0;
433	    this.startup_time = Date.now();
434	
435	    // optional , but when used we store signing state in this object: 
436	    this.signing = new MAVLinkSigning();
437	}
438	
439	// Implements EventEmitter
440	util.inherits(${MAVPROCESSOR}, events.EventEmitter);
441	
442	// If the logger exists, this function will add a message to it.
443	// Assumes the logger is a winston object.
444	${MAVPROCESSOR}.prototype.log = function(message) {
445	    if(this.logger) {
446	        this.logger.info(message);
447	    }
448	}
449	
450	${MAVPROCESSOR}.prototype.log = function(level, message) {
451	    if(this.logger) {
452	        this.logger.log(level, message);
453	    }
454	}
455	
456	${MAVPROCESSOR}.prototype.send = function(mavmsg) {
457	    buf = mavmsg.pack(this);
458	    this.file.write(buf);
459	    this.seq = (this.seq + 1) % 256;
460	    this.total_packets_sent +=1;
461	    this.total_bytes_sent += buf.length;
462	}
463	
464	// return number of bytes needed for next parsing stage
465	${MAVPROCESSOR}.prototype.bytes_needed = function() {
466	    ret = this.expected_length - this.buf.length;
467	    return ( ret <= 0 ) ? 1 : ret;
468	}
469	
470	// add data to the local buffer
471	${MAVPROCESSOR}.prototype.pushBuffer = function(data) {
472	    if(data) {
473	        this.buf = Buffer.concat([this.buf, data]);   // python calls this self.buf.extend(c) 
474	        this.total_bytes_received += data.length;
475	    }
476	}
477	
478	// Decode prefix.  Elides the prefix.
479	${MAVPROCESSOR}.prototype.parsePrefix = function() {
480	
481	    // Test for a message prefix.
482	    if( this.buf.length >= 1 && this.buf[0] != this.protocol_marker ) {
483	
484	        // Strip the offending initial byte and throw an error.
485	        var badPrefix = this.buf[0];
486	        this.bufInError = this.buf.slice(0,1);
487	        this.buf = this.buf.slice(1);
488	        this.expected_length = ${MAVHEAD}.HEADER_LEN; //initially we 'expect' at least the length of the header, later parseLength corrects for this. 
489	        throw new Error("Bad prefix ("+badPrefix+")");
490	    }
491	
492	}
493	
494	// Determine the length.  Leaves buffer untouched.
495	// Although the 'len' of a packet is available as of the second byte, the third byte with 'incompat_flags' lets
496	//  us know if we have signing enabled, which affects the real-world length by the signature-block length of 13 bytes.
497	// once successful, 'this.expected_length' is correctly set for the whole packet.
498	${MAVPROCESSOR}.prototype.parseLength = function() {
499	    
500	    if( this.buf.length >= 3 ) { 
501	        var unpacked = jspack.Unpack('BBB', this.buf.slice(0, 3)); 
502	        var magic = unpacked[0]; // stx ie fd or fe etc 
503	        this.expected_length = unpacked[1] + ${MAVHEAD}.HEADER_LEN + 2 // length of message + header + CRC (ie non-signed length) 
504	        this.incompat_flags = unpacked[2];  
505	        // mavlink2 only..  in mavlink1, incompat_flags var above is actually the 'seq', but for this test its ok. 
506	        if ((magic == ${MAVHEAD}.PROTOCOL_MARKER_V2 ) && ( this.incompat_flags & ${MAVHEAD}.MAVLINK_IFLAG_SIGNED )){ 
507	            this.expected_length += ${MAVHEAD}.MAVLINK_SIGNATURE_BLOCK_LEN; 
508	        } 
509	    }
510	
511	}
512	
513	// input some data bytes, possibly returning a new message - python equiv function is called parse_char / __parse_char_legacy 
514	${MAVPROCESSOR}.prototype.parseChar = function(c) {
515	
516	    var m = null;
517	
518	    try {
519	
520	        this.pushBuffer(c);
521	        this.parsePrefix();
522	        this.parseLength();
523	        m = this.parsePayload();
524	
525	    } catch(e) {
526	
527	        this.log('error', e.message);
528	        this.total_receive_errors += 1;
529	        m = new ${MAVHEAD}.messages.bad_data(this.bufInError, e.message);
530	        this.bufInError = new Buffer.from([]);
531	        
532	    }
533	
534	    // emit a packet-specific message as well as a generic message, user/s can choose to use either or both of these.
535	    if(null != m) {
536	        this.emit(m._name, m);
537	        this.emit('message', m);
538	    }
539	
540	    return m;
541	
542	}
543	
544	// continuation of python's  __parse_char_legacy 
545	${MAVPROCESSOR}.prototype.parsePayload = function() {
546	
547	    var m = null;
548	
549	    // tip: this.expected_length and this.incompat_flags both already set correctly by parseLength(..) above 
550	
551	    // If we have enough bytes to try and read it, read it.  
552	    //  shortest packet is header+checksum(2) with no payload, so we need at least that many 
553	    //  but once we have a longer 'expected length' we have to read all of it. 
554	    if(( this.expected_length >= ${MAVHEAD}.HEADER_LEN+2) && (this.buf.length >= this.expected_length) ) { 
555	
556	        // Slice off the expected packet length, reset expectation to be to find a header.
557	        var mbuf = this.buf.slice(0, this.expected_length);
558	
559	        // TODO: slicing off the buffer should depend on the error produced by the decode() function
560	        // - if we find a well formed message, cut-off the expected_length 
561	        // - if the message is not well formed (correct prefix by accident), cut-off 1 char only
562	        this.buf = this.buf.slice(this.expected_length);
563	        this.expected_length = ${MAVHEAD}.HEADER_LEN; // after attempting a parse, we'll next expect to find just a header. 
564	
565	        try {
566	            m = this.decode(mbuf);
567	            this.total_packets_received += 1;
568	        }
569	        catch(e) {
570	            // Set buffer in question and re-throw to generic error handling
571	            this.bufInError = mbuf;
572	            throw e;
573	        }
574	    }
575	
576	    return m;
577	
578	}
579	
580	// input some data bytes, possibly returning an array of new messages
581	${MAVPROCESSOR}.prototype.parseBuffer = function(s) {
582	    
583	    // Get a message, if one is available in the stream.
584	    var m = this.parseChar(s);
585	
586	    // No messages available, bail.
587	    if ( null === m ) {
588	        return null;
589	    }
590	    
591	    // While more valid messages can be read from the existing buffer, add
592	    // them to the array of new messages and return them.
593	    var ret = [m];
594	    while(true) {
595	        m = this.parseChar();
596	        if ( null === m ) {
597	            // No more messages left.
598	            return ret;
599	        }
600	        ret.push(m);
601	    }
602	
603	}
604	
605	// from Buffer to ArrayBuffer 
606	function toArrayBuffer(buf) { 
607	    var ab = new ArrayBuffer(buf.length); 
608	    var view = new Uint8Array(ab); 
609	    for (var i = 0; i < buf.length; ++i) { 
610	        view[i] = buf[i]; 
611	    } 
612	    return ab; 
613	} 
614	// and back 
615	function toBuffer(ab) { 
616	    var buf = Buffer.alloc(ab.byteLength); 
617	    var view = new Uint8Array(ab); 
618	    for (var i = 0; i < buf.length; ++i) { 
619	        buf[i] = view[i]; 
620	    } 
621	    return buf; 
622	} 
623	 
624	//check signature on incoming message , many of the comments in this file come from the python impl
625	${MAVPROCESSOR}.prototype.check_signature = function(msgbuf, srcSystem, srcComponent) { 
626	
627	        //if (isinstance(msgbuf, array.array)){ 
628	        //    msgbuf = msgbuf.tostring() 
629	        //} 
630	        if ( Buffer.isBuffer(msgbuf) ) { 
631	            msgbuf = toArrayBuffer(msgbuf); 
632	        } 
633	 
634	        //timestamp_buf = msgbuf[-12:-6] 
635	        var timestamp_buf= msgbuf.slice(-12,-6);  
636	 
637	        //link_id = msgbuf[-13] 
638	        var link_id= new Buffer.from(msgbuf.slice(-13,-12)); // just a single byte really, but returned as a buffer 
639	        link_id = link_id[0]; // get the first byte.
640	 
641	        //self.mav_sign_unpacker = jspack.Unpack('<IH') 
642	        // (tlow, thigh) = self.mav_sign_unpacker.unpack(timestamp_buf) 
643	
644	        // I means unsigned 4bytes, H means unsigned 2 bytes
645	        var t = jspack.Unpack('<IH',new Buffer.from(timestamp_buf))  
646	        const [tlow, thigh]  = t; 
647	 
648	        // due to js not being able to shift numbers  more than 32, we'll use this instead.. 
649	        // js stores all its numbers as a 64bit float with 53 bits of mantissa, so have room for 48 ok. 
650	        function shift(number, shift) { 
651	            return number * Math.pow(2, shift); 
652	        } 
653	        var thigh_shifted = shift(thigh,32);  
654	        var timestamp = tlow + thigh_shifted 
655	 
656	        // see if the timestamp is acceptable 
657	 
658	         // we'll use a STRING containing these three things in it as a unique key eg: '0,1,1' 
659	        stream_key = new Array(link_id,srcSystem,srcComponent).toString(); 
660	 
661	        if (stream_key in this.signing.stream_timestamps){ 
662	            if (timestamp <= this.signing.stream_timestamps[stream_key]){ 
663	                //# reject old timestamp 
664	                //console.log('old timestamp')  
665	                return false 
666	            } 
667	        }else{ 
668	            //# a new stream has appeared. Accept the timestamp if it is at most 
669	            //# one minute behind our current timestamp 
670	            if (timestamp + 6000*1000 < this.signing.timestamp){ 
671	                //console.log('bad new stream ', timestamp/(100.0*1000*60*60*24*365), this.signing.timestamp/(100.0*1000*60*60*24*365))  
672	                return false 
673	            } 
674	            this.signing.stream_timestamps[stream_key] = timestamp; 
675	            //console.log('new stream',this.signing.stream_timestamps)  
676	        } 
677	 
678	         //   h = hashlib.new('sha256') 
679	         //   h.update(this.signing.secret_key) 
680	         //   h.update(msgbuf[:-6]) 
681	        var crypto= require('crypto'); 
682	        var h =  crypto.createHash('sha256'); 
683	 
684	        // just the last 6 of 13 available are the actual sig . ie excluding the linkid(1) and timestamp(6) 
685	        var sigpart = msgbuf.slice(-6); 
686	        sigpart = new Buffer.from(sigpart); 
687	        // not sig part 0- end-minus-6 
688	        var notsigpart = msgbuf.slice(0,-6);  
689	        notsigpart = new Buffer.from(notsigpart); 
690	
691	        h.update(this.signing.secret_key); // secret is already a Buffer 
692	        //var tmp = h.copy().digest(); 
693	        h.update(notsigpart);  
694	        //var tmp2 = h.copy().digest() 
695	        var hashDigest = h.digest(); 
696	        sig1 = hashDigest.slice(0,6) 
697	 
698	        //sig1 = str(h.digest())[:6] 
699	        //sig2 = str(msgbuf)[-6:] 
700	
701	        // can't just compare sigs, need a full buffer compare like this... 
702	        //if (sig1 != sigpart){  
703	        if (Buffer.compare(sig1,sigpart)){  
704	            //console.log('sig mismatch',sig1,sigpart)  
705	            return false 
706	        } 
707	        //# the timestamp we next send with is the max of the received timestamp and 
708	        //# our current timestamp 
709	        this.signing.timestamp = Math.max(this.signing.timestamp, timestamp) 
710	        return true
711	} 
712	
713	/* decode a buffer as a MAVLink message */
714	${MAVPROCESSOR}.prototype.decode = function(msgbuf) {
715	
716	    var magic, incompat_flags, compat_flags, mlen, seq, srcSystem, srcComponent, unpacked, msgId, signature_len; 
717	
718	    // decode the header
719	    try {
720	        """, {'MAVPROCESSOR': get_mavprocessor(xml),
721	              'MAVHEAD': get_mavhead(xml),
722	              'PROTOCOL_MARKER': xml.protocol_marker})
723	    # Mavlink2 only

--------------------------------------------------
>> Issue: [B815:write] os.write
   Severity: High   Confidence: Medium
   Location: /home/blue/PyPIAgent/Dataset/study/unzip_benign/pymavlink-2.4.43/pymavlink-2.4.43/generator/mavgen_javascript.py:725
   More Info: https://bandit.readthedocs.io/en/latest/plugins/b815_write.html
724	    if (xml.protocol_marker == 253):
725	        t.write(outf, """
726	unpacked = jspack.Unpack('cBBBBBBHB', msgbuf.slice(0, 10));  // the H in here causes msgIDlow to takeup 2 bytes, the rest 1 
727	        magic = unpacked[0];
728	        mlen = unpacked[1];
729	        incompat_flags = unpacked[2];
730	        compat_flags = unpacked[3];
731	        seq = unpacked[4];
732	        srcSystem = unpacked[5];
733	        srcComponent = unpacked[6];
734	        var msgIDlow = ((unpacked[7] & 0xFF) << 8) | ((unpacked[7] >> 8) & 0xFF); // first-two msgid bytes 
735	        var msgIDhigh = unpacked[8];   // the 3rd msgid byte 
736	        msgId = msgIDlow | (msgIDhigh<<16);  // combined result. 0 - 16777215  24bit number 
737	        """, {'MAVHEAD': get_mavhead(xml)})
738	    # Mavlink1

   More Info: https://bandit.readthedocs.io/en/latest/plugins/b815_write.html

750	    t.write(outf, """
751	}
752	    catch(e) {
753	        throw new Error('Unable to unpack MAVLink header: ' + e.message);
754	    }
755	
756	    //  TODO allow full parsing of 1.0 inside the 2.0 parser, this is just a start 
757	    if (magic == ${MAVHEAD}.PROTOCOL_MARKER_V1){ 
758	            //headerlen = 6; 
759	             
760	            // these two are in the same place in both v1 and v2 so no change needed: 
761	            //magic = magic; 
762	            //mlen = mlen; 
763	 
764	            // grab mavlink-v1 header position info from v2 unpacked position 
765	            seq1 = incompat_flags; 
766	            srcSystem1 = compat_flags; 
767	            srcComponent1 = seq; 
768	            msgId1 = srcSystem; 
769	            // override the v1 vs v2 offsets so we get the correct data either way... 
770	            seq = seq1; 
771	            srcSystem = srcSystem1; 
772	            srcComponent = srcComponent1; 
773	            msgId = msgId1;  
774	            // don't exist in mavlink1, so zero-them 
775	            incompat_flags = 0; 
776	            compat_flags = 0; 
777	            signature_len = 0; 
778	            // todo add more v1 here and don't just return 
779	            return; 
780	    } 
781	
782	    if (magic.charCodeAt(0) != this.protocol_marker) {
783	        throw new Error("Invalid MAVLink prefix ("+magic.charCodeAt(0)+")");
784	    }
785	
786	    // is packet supposed to be signed? 
787	    if ( incompat_flags & ${MAVHEAD}.MAVLINK_IFLAG_SIGNED ){  
788	        signature_len = ${MAVHEAD}.MAVLINK_SIGNATURE_BLOCK_LEN; 
789	    } else { 
790	        signature_len = 0; 
791	    } 
792	 
793	    // header's declared len compared to packets actual len 
794	    var actual_len = (msgbuf.length - (${MAVHEAD}.HEADER_LEN + 2 + signature_len)); 
795	    var actual_len_nosign = (msgbuf.length - (${MAVHEAD}.HEADER_LEN + 2 )); 
796	 
797	    if ((mlen == actual_len) && (signature_len > 0)){ 
798	        var len_if_signed = mlen+signature_len; 
799	        //console.log("Packet appears signed && labeled as signed, OK. msgId=" + msgId);     
800	 
801	    } else  if ((mlen == actual_len_nosign) && (signature_len > 0)){ 
802	 
803	        var len_if_signed = mlen+signature_len; 
804	        throw new Error("Packet appears unsigned when labeled as signed. Got actual_len "+actual_len_nosign+" expected " + len_if_signed + ", msgId=" + msgId);     
805	 
806	    } else if( mlen != actual_len) {  
807	          throw new Error("Invalid MAVLink message length.  Got " + (msgbuf.length - (${MAVHEAD}.HEADER_LEN + 2)) + " expected " + mlen + ", msgId=" + msgId); 
808	
809	    }  
810	 
811	    if( false === _.has(${MAVHEAD}.map, msgId) ) {
812	        throw new Error("Unknown MAVLink message ID (" + msgId + ")");
813	    }
814	
815	    // here's the common chunks of packet we want to work with below.. 
816	    var headerBuf= msgbuf.slice(${MAVHEAD}.HEADER_LEN); // first10 
817	    var sigBuf = msgbuf.slice(-signature_len); // last 13 or nothing 
818	    var crcBuf1 = msgbuf.slice(-2); // either last-2 or last-2-prior-to-signature 
819	    var crcBuf2 = msgbuf.slice(-15,-13); // either last-2 or last-2-prior-to-signature 
820	    var payloadBuf = msgbuf.slice(${MAVHEAD}.HEADER_LEN, -(signature_len+2)); // the remaining bit between the header and the crc 
821	    var crcCheckBuf = msgbuf.slice(1, -(signature_len+2)); // the part uses to calculate the crc - ie between the magic and signature, 
822	
823	    // decode the payload
824	    // refs: (fmt, type, order_map, crc_extra) = ${MAVHEAD}.map[msgId]
825	    var decoder = ${MAVHEAD}.map[msgId];
826	
827	    // decode the checksum
828	    var receivedChecksum = undefined; 
829	    if ( signature_len == 0 ) { // unsigned 
830	        try { 
831	            receivedChecksum = jspack.Unpack('<H', crcBuf1); 
832	        } catch (e) { 
833	            throw new Error("Unable to unpack MAVLink unsigned CRC: " + e.message); 
834	        } 
835	    } else { // signed 
836	        try { 
837	            receivedChecksum = jspack.Unpack('<H', crcBuf2); 
838	        } catch (e) { 
839	            throw new Error("Unable to unpack MAVLink signed CRC: " + e.message); 
840	        } 
841	    }
842	    receivedChecksum = receivedChecksum[0]; 
843	
844	    // make our own chksum of the relevant part of the packet... 
845	    var messageChecksum = ${MAVHEAD}.x25Crc(crcCheckBuf);  
846	    var messageChecksum2 = ${MAVHEAD}.x25Crc([decoder.crc_extra], messageChecksum); 
847	 
848	    if ( receivedChecksum != messageChecksum2 ) { 
849	        throw new Error('invalid MAVLink CRC in msgID ' +msgId+ ', got ' + receivedChecksum + ' checksum, calculated payload checksum as '+messageChecksum2 );
850	    }
851	 
852	    // now check the signature... 
853	    var sig_ok = false 
854	    if (signature_len == ${MAVHEAD}.MAVLINK_SIGNATURE_BLOCK_LEN){ 
855	        this.signing.sig_count += 1  
856	    } 
857	
858	    // it's a Buffer, zero-length means unused 
859	    if (this.signing.secret_key.length != 0 ){ 
860	        var accept_signature = false; 
861	        if (signature_len == ${MAVHEAD}.MAVLINK_SIGNATURE_BLOCK_LEN){  
862	            sig_ok = this.check_signature(msgbuf, srcSystem, srcComponent); 
863	            accept_signature = sig_ok; 
864	            if (sig_ok){ 
865	                this.signing.goodsig_count += 1 
866	            }else{ 
867	                this.signing.badsig_count += 1 
868	            } 
869	            if ( (! accept_signature) && (this.signing.allow_unsigned_callback != undefined) ){ 
870	                accept_signature = this.signing.allow_unsigned_callback(this, msgId); 
871	                if (accept_signature){ 
872	                    this.signing.unsigned_count += 1 
873	                }else{ 
874	                    this.signing.reject_count += 1 
875	                } 
876	            } 
877	        }else if (this.signing.allow_unsigned_callback != undefined){ 
878	            accept_signature = this.signing.allow_unsigned_callback(this, msgId); 
879	            if (accept_signature){ 
880	                this.signing.unsigned_count += 1 
881	            }else{ 
882	                this.signing.reject_count += 1 
883	            } 
884	        } 
885	        if (!accept_signature) throw new Error('Invalid signature'); 
886	    } 
887	
888	    // now look at the specifics of the payload... 
889	    var paylen = jspack.CalcLength(decoder.format);
890	
891	    """, {'MAVPROCESSOR': get_mavprocessor(xml),
892	          'MAVHEAD': get_mavhead(xml)})

903	    t.write(outf, """
904	    // Decode the payload and reorder the fields to match the order map.
905	    try {
906	        var t = jspack.Unpack(decoder.format, payloadBuf); 
907	    }
908	    catch (e) {
909	        throw new Error('Unable to unpack MAVLink payload type='+decoder.type+' format='+decoder.format+' payloadLength='+ payloadBuf +': '+ e.message); 
910	    }
911	
912	    // Need to check if the message contains arrays
913	    var args = {};
914	    const elementsInMsg = decoder.order_map.length;
915	    const actualElementsInMsg = JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(t)).length;
916	
917	    if (elementsInMsg == actualElementsInMsg) {
918	        // Reorder the fields to match the order map
919	        _.each(t, function(e, i, l) {
920	            args[i] = t[decoder.order_map[i]]
921	        });
922	    } else {
923	        // This message contains arrays
924	        var typeIndex = 1;
925	        var orderIndex = 0;
926	        var memberIndex = 0;
927	        var tempArgs = {};
928	
929	        // Walk through the fields 
930	        for(var i = 0, size = decoder.format.length-1; i <= size; ++i) {
931	            var order = decoder.order_map[orderIndex];
932	            var currentType =  decoder.format[typeIndex];
933	
934	            if (isNaN(parseInt(currentType))) {
935	                // This field is not an array check the type and add it to the args
936	                tempArgs[orderIndex] = t[memberIndex];
937	                memberIndex++;
938	            } else {
939	                // This field is part of an array, need to find the length of the array
940	                var arraySize = ''
941	                var newArray = []
942	                while (!isNaN(decoder.format[typeIndex])) {
943	                    arraySize = arraySize + decoder.format[typeIndex];
944	                    typeIndex++;
945	                }
946	
947	                // Now that we know how long the array is, create an array with the values
948	                for(var j = 0, size = parseInt(arraySize); j < size; ++j){
949	                    newArray.push(t[j+orderIndex]);
950	                    memberIndex++;
951	                }
952	
953	                // Add the array to the args object
954	                arraySize = arraySize + decoder.format[typeIndex];
955	                currentType = arraySize;
956	                tempArgs[orderIndex] = newArray;
957	            }
958	            orderIndex++;
959	            typeIndex++;
960	        }
961	
962	        // Finally reorder the fields to match the order map
963	        _.each(t, function(e, i, l) {
964	            args[i] = tempArgs[decoder.order_map[i]]
965	        });
966	    }
967	
968	    
969	
970	    // construct the message object
971	    try {
972	        // args at this point might look like:  { '0': 6, '1': 8, '2': 0, '3': 0, '4': 3, '5': 3 }
973	        var m = new decoder.type();   // make a new 'empty' instance of the right class,
974	        m.set(args,false); // associate ordered-field-numbers to names, after construction not during.
975	    }
976	    catch (e) {
977	        throw new Error('Unable to instantiate MAVLink message of type '+decoder.type+' : ' + e.message);
978	    }
979	
980	    m._signed = sig_ok; 
981	    if (m._signed) { m._link_id = msgbuf[-13]; } 
982	 
983	    m._msgbuf = msgbuf;
984	    m._payload = payloadBuf 
985	    m.crc = receivedChecksum;
986	    m._header = new ${MAVHEAD}.header(msgId, mlen, seq, srcSystem, srcComponent, incompat_flags, compat_flags);
987	    this.log(m);
988	    return m;
989	}

991	""", {'MAVHEAD': get_mavhead(xml), 'MAVPROCESSOR': get_mavprocessor(xml), 'PROTOCOL_MARKER' : xml.protocol_marker})

42	Buffer.prototype.toByteArray = function () {
43	  return Array.prototype.slice.call(this, 0)
44	}
45	
46	${MAVHEAD} = function(){};
47	
48	// Implement the CRC-16/MCRF4XX function (present in the Python version through the mavutil.py package)
49	${MAVHEAD}.x25Crc = function(buffer, crcIN) {
50	
51	    var bytes = buffer;
52	    var crcOUT = crcIN ===  undefined ? 0xffff : crcIN;
53	    _.each(bytes, function(e) {
54	        var tmp = e ^ (crcOUT & 0xff);
55	        tmp = (tmp ^ (tmp << 4)) & 0xff;
56	        crcOUT = (crcOUT >> 8) ^ (tmp << 8) ^ (tmp << 3) ^ (tmp >> 4);
57	        crcOUT = crcOUT & 0xffff;
58	    });
59	    return crcOUT;
60	
61	}

90

318	   
319	    this.srcSystem = (typeof srcSystem === 'undefined') ? 0 : srcSystem;
320	    this.srcComponent =  (typeof srcComponent === 'undefined') ? 0 : srcComponent;
321	
322	    this.have_prefix_error = false;
323	
324	    // The first packet we expect is a valid header, 6 bytes.
325	    this.protocol_marker = ${PROTOCOL_MARKER};   
326	    this.expected_length = ${MAVHEAD}.HEADER_LEN;
327	    this.little_endian = true;
328	
329	    this.crc_extra = true;
330	    this.sort_fields = true;
331	    this.total_packets_sent = 0;
332	    this.total_bytes_sent = 0;
333	    this.total_packets_received = 0;
334	    this.total_bytes_received = 0;
335	    this.total_receive_errors = 0;
336	    this.startup_time = Date.now();
337	    
338	}
339	
340	// Implements EventEmitter
341	util.inherits(${MAVPROCESSOR}, events.EventEmitter);
342	
343	// If the logger exists, this function will add a message to it.
344	// Assumes the logger is a winston object.
345	${MAVPROCESSOR}.prototype.log = function(message) {
346	    if(this.logger) {
347	        this.logger.info(message);
348	    }
349	}
350	
351	${MAVPROCESSOR}.prototype.log = function(level, message) {
352	    if(this.logger) {
353	        this.logger.log(level, message);
354	    }
355	}
356	
357	${MAVPROCESSOR}.prototype.send = function(mavmsg) {
358	    buf = mavmsg.pack(this);
359	    this.file.write(buf);
360	    this.seq = (this.seq + 1) % 256;
361	    this.total_packets_sent +=1;
362	    this.total_bytes_sent += buf.length;
363	}
364	
365	// return number of bytes needed for next parsing stage
366	${MAVPROCESSOR}.prototype.bytes_needed = function() {
367	    ret = this.expected_length - this.buf.length;
368	    return ( ret <= 0 ) ? 1 : ret;
369	}
370	
371	// add data to the local buffer
372	${MAVPROCESSOR}.prototype.pushBuffer = function(data) {
373	    if(data) {
374	        this.buf = Buffer.concat([this.buf, data]);
375	        this.total_bytes_received += data.length;
376	    }
377	}
378	
379	// Decode prefix.  Elides the prefix.
380	${MAVPROCESSOR}.prototype.parsePrefix = function() {
381	
382	    // Test for a message prefix.
383	    if( this.buf.length >= 1 && this.buf[0] != this.protocol_marker ) {
384	
385	        // Strip the offending initial byte and throw an error.
386	        var badPrefix = this.buf[0];
387	        this.bufInError = this.buf.slice(0,1);
388	        this.buf = this.buf.slice(1);
389	        this.expected_length = ${MAVHEAD}.HEADER_LEN;
390	
391	        // TODO: enable subsequent prefix error suppression if robust_parsing is implemented
392	        //if(!this.have_prefix_error) {
393	        //    this.have_prefix_error = true;
394	            throw new Error("Bad prefix ("+badPrefix+")");
395	        //}
396	
397	    }
398	    //else if( this.buf.length >= 1 && this.buf[0] == this.protocol_marker ) {
399	    //    this.have_prefix_error = false;
400	    //}
401	
402	}
403	
404	// Determine the length.  Leaves buffer untouched.
405	${MAVPROCESSOR}.prototype.parseLength = function() {
406	    
407	    if( this.buf.length >= 2 ) {
408	        var unpacked = jspack.Unpack('BB', this.buf.slice(0, 2));
409	        this.expected_length = unpacked[1] + ${MAVHEAD}.HEADER_LEN + 2 // length of message + header + CRC
410	    }
411	
412	}
413	
414	// input some data bytes, possibly returning a new message
415	${MAVPROCESSOR}.prototype.parseChar = function(c) {
416	
417	    var m = null;
418	
419	    try {
420	
421	        this.pushBuffer(c);
422	        this.parsePrefix();
423	        this.parseLength();
424	        m = this.parsePayload();
425	
426	    } catch(e) {
427	
428	        this.log('error', e.message);
429	        this.total_receive_errors += 1;
430	        m = new ${MAVHEAD}.messages.bad_data(this.bufInError, e.message);
431	        this.bufInError = new Buffer.from([]);
432	        
433	    }
434	
435	    if(null != m) {
436	        this.emit(m.name, m);
437	        this.emit('message', m);
438	    }
439	
440	    return m;
441	
442	}
443	
444	${MAVPROCESSOR}.prototype.parsePayload = function() {
445	
446	    var m = null;
447	
448	    // If we have enough bytes to try and read it, read it.
449	    if( this.expected_length >= 8 && this.buf.length >= this.expected_length ) {
450	
451	        // Slice off the expected packet length, reset expectation to be to find a header.
452	        var mbuf = this.buf.slice(0, this.expected_length);
453	        // TODO: slicing off the buffer should depend on the error produced by the decode() function
454	        // - if a message we find a well formed message, cut-off the expected_length
455	        // - if the message is not well formed (correct prefix by accident), cut-off 1 char only
456	        this.buf = this.buf.slice(this.expected_length);
457	        this.expected_length = 6;
458	
459	        // w.info("Attempting to parse packet, message candidate buffer is ["+mbuf.toByteArray()+"]");
460	
461	        try {
462	            m = this.decode(mbuf);
463	            this.total_packets_received += 1;
464	        }
465	        catch(e) {
466	            // Set buffer in question and re-throw to generic error handling
467	            this.bufInError = mbuf;
468	            throw e;
469	        }
470	    }
471	
472	    return m;
473	
474	}
475	
476	// input some data bytes, possibly returning an array of new messages
477	${MAVPROCESSOR}.prototype.parseBuffer = function(s) {
478	    
479	    // Get a message, if one is available in the stream.
480	    var m = this.parseChar(s);
481	
482	    // No messages available, bail.
483	    if ( null === m ) {
484	        return null;
485	    }
486	    
487	    // While more valid messages can be read from the existing buffer, add
488	    // them to the array of new messages and return them.
489	    var ret = [m];
490	    while(true) {
491	        m = this.parseChar();
492	        if ( null === m ) {
493	            // No more messages left.
494	            return ret;
495	        }
496	        ret.push(m);
497	    }
498	
499	}
500

592	    // Decode the payload and reorder the fields to match the order map.
593	    try {
594	        var t = jspack.Unpack(decoder.format, payload);
595	    }
596	    catch (e) {
597	        throw new Error('Unable to unpack MAVLink payload type='+decoder.type+' format='+decoder.format+' payloadLength='+ payload +': '+ e.message);
598	    }

602	    const elementsInMsg = decoder.order_map.length;
603	    const actualElementsInMsg = JSON.parse(JSON.stringify(t)).length;
604	
605	    if (elementsInMsg == actualElementsInMsg) {
606	        // Reorder the fields to match the order map
607	        _.each(t, function(e, i, l) {
608	            args[i] = t[decoder.order_map[i]]
609	        });
610	    } else {
611	        // This message contains arrays
612	        var typeIndex = 1;
613	        var orderIndex = 0;
614	        var memberIndex = 0;
615	        var tempArgs = {};
616	
617	        // Walk through the fields 
618	        for(var i = 0, size = decoder.format.length-1; i <= size; ++i) {
619	            var order = decoder.order_map[orderIndex];
620	            var currentType =  decoder.format[typeIndex];
621	
622	            if (isNaN(parseInt(currentType))) {
623	                // This field is not an array check the type and add it to the args
624	                tempArgs[orderIndex] = t[memberIndex];
625	                memberIndex++;
626	            } else {
627	                // This field is part of an array, need to find the length of the array
628	                var arraySize = ''
629	                var newArray = []
630	                while (!isNaN(decoder.format[typeIndex])) {
631	                    arraySize = arraySize + decoder.format[typeIndex];
632	                    typeIndex++;
633	                }
634	
635	                // Now that we know how long the array is, create an array with the values
636	                for(var j = 0, size = parseInt(arraySize); j < size; ++j){

639	                }

642	                arraySize = arraySize + decoder.format[typeIndex];
643	                currentType = arraySize;

647	            typeIndex++;
648	        }
649

653	        });
