71	"""-- Auto generated MAVLink parsing script
72	local mavlink_msgs = {{}}
73	
74	---Lookup the message id for a given message name
75	---@param msgname string
76	---@return integer -- message id
77	function mavlink_msgs.get_msgid(msgname)
78	  local message_map = require("{module_root_rel}mavlink_msg_" .. msgname)
79	  if not message_map then
80	    error("Unknown MAVLink message " .. msgname)
81	  end
82	  return message_map.id
83	end
84	
85	---Return a object containing everything that is not the payload
86	---@param message any -- encoded message
87	---@return table
88	function mavlink_msgs.decode_header(message)
89	  -- build up a map of the result
90	  local result = {{}}
91	
92	  result.checksum = string.unpack("<H", message, 1)
93	
94	  -- id the MAVLink version
95	  local magic = string.unpack("<B", message, 3)
96	  if (magic == 0xFE) then -- mavlink 1
97	    result.protocol_version = 1
98	  elseif (magic == 0XFD) then --mavlink 2
99	    result.protocol_version = 2
100	  else
101	    error("Invalid magic byte")
102	  end
103	
104	  -- fetch payload length
105	  result.payload_length = string.unpack("<B", message, 4)
106	
107	  -- fetch the incompat/compat flags
108	  result.incompat_flags, result.compat_flags = string.unpack("<BB", message, 5)
109	
110	  -- fetch seq/sysid/compid
111	  result.seq, result.sysid, result.compid = string.unpack("<BBB", message, 7)
112	
113	  -- fetch the message id
114	  result.msgid = string.unpack("<I3", message, 10)
115	
116	  return result
117	end
118	
119	-- generate the x25crc for a given buffer
120	---@param buffer string -- buffer to crc
121	---@return integer -- resulting crc 0 to 0xFFFF
122	function mavlink_msgs.generateCRC(buffer)
123	  -- generate the x25crc for a given buffer.
124	  local crc = 0xFFFF
125	  for i = 1, #buffer do
126	      local tmp = string.byte(buffer, i, i) ~ (crc & 0xFF)
127	      tmp = (tmp ~ (tmp << 4)) & 0xFF
128	      crc = (crc >> 8) ~ (tmp << 8) ~ (tmp << 3) ~ (tmp >> 4)
129	      crc = crc & 0xFFFF
130	  end
131	  return crc
132	end
133	
134	-- Note that this does not parse the serial data, it parses the MAVLink 2 C structure `mavlink_message_t`
135	-- This structure is passed in by the ArduPilot bindings as a string
136	---@param message any -- encoded message
137	---@param msg_map table -- table containing message objects with keys of the message ID
138	---@return table|nil -- a table representing the contents of the message, or nill if decode failed
139	function mavlink_msgs.decode(message, msg_map)
140	  local result = mavlink_msgs.decode_header(message)
141	  local message_map = require("{module_root_rel}mavlink_msg_" .. msg_map[result.msgid])
142	  if not message_map then
143	    -- we don't know how to decode this message, bail on it
144	    return nil
145	  end
146	
147	  -- If we have a crc extra for this message then check it
148	  -- This ensures compatibility with message definitions generated before the crc check was added
149	  if message_map.crc_extra then
150	    -- crc of payload and header values
151	    local crc_buffer
152	    if result.protocol_version == 2 then
153	      crc_buffer = string.sub(message, 4, 12 + result.payload_length)
154	
155	    else
156	      -- V1 does not include all fields on the wire
157	      crc_buffer = string.char(result.payload_length)
158	      crc_buffer = crc_buffer .. string.char(result.seq)
159	      crc_buffer = crc_buffer .. string.char(result.sysid)
160	      crc_buffer = crc_buffer .. string.char(result.compid)
161	      crc_buffer = crc_buffer .. string.char(result.msgid)
162	      if result.payload_length > 0 then
163	        crc_buffer = crc_buffer .. string.sub(message, 13, 12 + result.payload_length)
164	      end
165	
166	    end
167	
168	    local crc = mavlink_msgs.generateCRC(crc_buffer .. string.char(message_map.crc_extra))
169	
170	    if crc ~= result.checksum then
171	      -- crc failed
172	      return nil
173	    end
174	  end
175	
176	  -- map all the fields out
177	  local offset = 13
178	  for _,v in ipairs(message_map.fields) do
179	    if v[3] then
180	      result[v[1]] = {{}}
181	      for j=1,v[3] do
182	        result[v[1]][j], offset = string.unpack(v[2], message, offset)
183	      end
184	    else
185	      result[v[1]], offset = string.unpack(v[2], message, offset)
186	      if string.sub(v[2],2,2) == 'c' then
187	        -- Got string, unpack includes 0 values to the set length
188	        -- this is annoying, so remove them
189	        result[v[1]] = string.gsub(result[v[1]], string.char(0), "")
190	      end
191	    end
192	  end
193	
194	  return result
195	end
196	
197	---Encode the payload section of a given message
198	---@param msgname string -- name of message to encode
199	---@param message table -- table containing key value pairs representing the data fields in the message
200	---@return integer -- message id
201	---@return string -- encoded payload
202	function mavlink_msgs.encode(msgname, message)
203	  local message_map = require("{module_root_rel}mavlink_msg_" .. msgname)
204	  if not message_map then
205	    -- we don't know how to encode this message, bail on it
206	    error("Unknown MAVLink message " .. msgname)
207	  end
208	
209	  local packString = "<"
210	  local packedTable = {{}}
211	  local packedIndex = 1
212	  for i,v in ipairs(message_map.fields) do
213	    if v[3] then
214	      packString = (packString .. string.rep(string.sub(v[2], 2), v[3]))
215	      for j = 1, v[3] do
216	        packedTable[packedIndex] = message[message_map.fields[i][1]][j]
217	        if packedTable[packedIndex] == nil then
218	          packedTable[packedIndex] = 0
219	        end
220	        packedIndex = packedIndex + 1
221	      end
222	    else
223	      packString = (packString .. string.sub(v[2], 2))
224	      packedTable[packedIndex] = message[message_map.fields[i][1]]
225	      packedIndex = packedIndex + 1
226	    end
227	  end
228	  return message_map.id, string.pack(packString, table.unpack(packedTable))
229	end
230	
231	return mavlink_msgs
232	""".format(module_root_rel=module_root_rel))
233	    outf.close()

31	@class MVMavlink;

33	
34	@protocol MVMavlinkDelegate <NSObject>
35	
36	/*!
37	 Method called on the delegate when a full message has been received. Note that this may be called multiple times when parseData: is called, if the data passed to parseData: contains multiple messages.
38	
39	 @param mavlink The MVMavlink object calling this method
40	 @param message The id<MVMessage> class containing the parsed message
41	 */
42	- (void)mavlink:(MVMavlink *)mavlink didGetMessage:(id<MVMessage>)message;
43	
44	/*!
45	 Method called on the delegate when data should be sent.
46	
47	 @param mavlink The MVMavlink object calling this method
48	 @param data NSData object containing the bytes to be sent
49	 */
50	- (BOOL)mavlink:(MVMavlink *)mavlink shouldWriteData:(NSData *)data;
51	
52	@end
53	
54	/*!
55	 Class for parsing and sending instances of id<MVMessage>
56	
57	 @discussion MVMavlink receives a stream of bytes via the parseData: method and calls the delegate method mavlink:didGetMessage: each time a message is fully parsed. Users of MVMavlink can call parseData: anytime they get new data, even if that data does not contain a complete message.
58	 */
59	@interface MVMavlink : NSObject
60	@property (weak, nonatomic) id<MVMavlinkDelegate> delegate;
61	
62	/*!
63	 Parse byte data received from a MAVLink byte stream.
64	
65	 @param data NSData containing the received bytes
66	 */
67	- (void)parseData:(NSData *)data;
68	
69	/*!
70	 Compile MVMessage object into a bytes and pass to the delegate for sending.
71	
72	 @param message Object conforming to the MVMessage protocol that represents the data to be sent
73	 @return YES if message sending was successful
74	 */
75	- (BOOL)sendMessage:(id<MVMessage>)message;
76	
77	@end
78	''', xml)

94	- (void)parseData:(NSData *)data {
95	  mavlink_message_t msg;
96	  mavlink_status_t status;
97	  char *bytes = (char *)[data bytes];
98	
99	  for (NSInteger i = 0; i < [data length]; ++i) {
100	    if (mavlink_parse_char(MAVLINK_COMM_0, bytes[i], &msg, &status)) {
101	      // Packet received
102	      id<MVMessage> message = [MVMessage messageWithCMessage:msg];
103	      [_delegate mavlink:self didGetMessage:message];
104	    }
105	  }
106	}
107	
108	- (BOOL)sendMessage:(id<MVMessage>)message {
109	  return [_delegate mavlink:self shouldWriteData:[message data]];
110	}

178	+ (id)messageWithCMessage:(mavlink_message_t)message {
179	  static NSDictionary *messageIdToClass = nil;
180	  if (!messageIdToClass) {
181	    messageIdToClass = @{
182	${{message:      @${id} : [MVMessage${name_camel_case} class],
183	}}
184	    };
185	  }
186	
187	  Class messageClass = messageIdToClass[@(message.msgid)];
188	  // Store unknown messages to MVMessage
189	  if (!messageClass) {
190	    messageClass = [MVMessage class];
191	  }
192	
193	  return [[messageClass alloc] initWithCMessage:message];
194	}
195

197	  if ((self = [super init])) {
198	    self->_message = message;
199	  }
200	  return self;
201	}

205	
206	  NSInteger length = mavlink_msg_to_send_buffer(buffer, &self->_message);
207	
208	  return [NSData dataWithBytes:buffer length:length];
209	}
210	
211	- (uint8_t)systemId {
212	  return self->_message.sysid;
213	}
214	
215	- (uint8_t)componentId {
216	  return self->_message.compid;
217	}
218	
219	- (uint8_t)messageId {
220	  return self->_message.msgid;
221	}

171	class x25crc(object):
172	    """CRC-16/MCRF4XX - based on checksum.h from mavlink library"""
173	
174	    def __init__(self, buf${type_optional_intseq_default})${type_none_ret}:
175	        self.crc = 0xFFFF
176	        if buf is not None:
177	            self.accumulate(buf)
178	
179	    def accumulate(self, buf${type_intseq})${type_none_ret}:
180	        """add in some more bytes (it also accepts python2 strings)"""
181	        if sys.version_info[0] == 2 and type(buf) is str:
182	            buf = bytearray(buf)

184	        accum = self.crc
185	        for b in buf:
186	            tmp = b ^ (accum & 0xFF)
187	            tmp = (tmp ^ (tmp << 4)) & 0xFF
188	            accum = (accum >> 8) ^ (tmp << 8) ^ (tmp << 3) ^ (tmp >> 4)

366	    def _pack(self, mav${type_mavlink}, crc_extra${type_int}, payload${type_bytes}, force_mavlink1${type_bool_default})${type_bytes_ret}:

368	        if float(WIRE_PROTOCOL_VERSION) == 2.0 and not force_mavlink1:
369	            # in MAVLink2 we can strip trailing zeros off payloads. This allows for simple
370	            # variable length arrays and smaller packets

399	            self.sign_packet(mav)

768	class MAVError(Exception):
769	    """MAVLink error class"""
770	
771	    def __init__(self, msg${type_str})${type_none_ret}:
772	        Exception.__init__(self, msg)
773	        self.message = msg
774	
775	
776	class MAVLink_bad_data(MAVLink_message):
777	    """
778	    a piece of bad data in a mavlink stream
779	    """
780	
781	    def __init__(self, data${type_bytes}, reason${type_str})${type_none_ret}:
782	        MAVLink_message.__init__(self, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_BAD_DATA, "BAD_DATA")
783	        self._fieldnames = ["data", "reason"]
784	        self.data = data
785	        self.reason = reason
786	        self._msgbuf = bytearray(data)
787	        self._instance_field = None
788	
789	    def __str__(self)${type_str_ret}:
790	        """Override the __str__ function from MAVLink_messages because non-printable characters are common in to be the reason for this message to exist."""
791	        if sys.version_info[0] == 2:
792	            hexstr = ["{:x}".format(ord(i)) for i in self.data]
793	        else:
794	            hexstr = ["{:x}".format(i) for i in self.data]
795	        return "%s {%s, data:%s}" % (self._type, self.reason, hexstr)
796	
797	
798	class MAVLink_unknown(MAVLink_message):
799	    """
800	    a message that we don't have in the XML used when built
801	    """
802	
803	    def __init__(self, msgid${type_int}, data${type_bytes})${type_none_ret}:
804	        MAVLink_message.__init__(self, MAVLINK_MSG_ID_UNKNOWN, "UNKNOWN_%u" % msgid)
805	        self._fieldnames = ["data"]
806	        self.data = data
807	        self._msgbuf = bytearray(data)
808	        self._instance_field = None
809	
810	    def __str__(self)${type_str_ret}:
811	        """Override the __str__ function from MAVLink_messages because non-printable characters are common."""
812	        if sys.version_info[0] == 2:
813	            hexstr = ["{:x}".format(ord(i)) for i in self.data]
814	        else:
815	            hexstr = ["{:x}".format(i) for i in self.data]
816	        return "%s {data:%s}" % (self._type, hexstr)
817	
818	
819	class MAVLinkSigning(object):
820	    """MAVLink signing state class"""
821	
822	    def __init__(self)${type_none_ret}:
823	        self.secret_key${type_optional_bytes} = None
824	        self.timestamp = 0
825	        self.link_id = 0
826	        self.sign_outgoing = False
827	        self.allow_unsigned_callback${type_optional_mavlink_message_signed_callback} = None
828	        self.stream_timestamps${type_dict_int_int_int_to_int} = {}
829	        self.sig_count = 0
830	        self.badsig_count = 0
831	        self.goodsig_count = 0
832	        self.unsigned_count = 0
833	        self.reject_count = 0
834	
835	
836	class MAVLink(object):
837	    """MAVLink protocol handling class"""
838	
839	    def __init__(self, file${type_any}, srcSystem${type_int_default}, srcComponent${type_int_default}, use_native${type_bool_default})${type_none_ret}:
840	        self.seq = 0
841	        self.file = file
842	        self.srcSystem = srcSystem
843	        self.srcComponent = srcComponent
844	        self.callback${type_optional_generic_callback} = None
845	        self.callback_args${type_optional_args} = None
846	        self.callback_kwargs${type_optional_kwargs} = None
847	        self.send_callback${type_optional_generic_callback} = None
848	        self.send_callback_args${type_optional_args} = None
849	        self.send_callback_kwargs${type_optional_kwargs} = None
850	        self.buf = bytearray()
851	        self.buf_index = 0
852	        self.expected_length = HEADER_LEN_V1 + 2
853	        self.have_prefix_error = False
854	        self.robust_parsing = False
855	        self.protocol_marker = ${protocol_marker}
856	        self.little_endian = ${little_endian}
857	        self.crc_extra = ${crc_extra}
858	        self.sort_fields = ${sort_fields}
859	        self.total_packets_sent = 0
860	        self.total_bytes_sent = 0
861	        self.total_packets_received = 0
862	        self.total_bytes_received = 0
863	        self.total_receive_errors = 0
864	        self.startup_time = time.time()
865	        self.signing = MAVLinkSigning()
866	        self.mav20_unpacker = struct.Struct("<cBBBBBBHB")
867	        self.mav10_unpacker = struct.Struct("<cBBBBB")
868	        self.mav20_h3_unpacker = struct.Struct("BBB")
869	        self.mav_csum_unpacker = struct.Struct("<H")
870	        self.mav_sign_unpacker = struct.Struct("<IH")
871	
872	    def set_callback(self, callback${type_generic_callback}, *args${type_any}, **kwargs${type_any})${type_none_ret}:
873	        self.callback = callback
874	        self.callback_args = args
875	        self.callback_kwargs = kwargs
876	
877	    def set_send_callback(self, callback${type_generic_callback}, *args${type_any}, **kwargs${type_any})${type_none_ret}:
878	        self.send_callback = callback
879	        self.send_callback_args = args
880	        self.send_callback_kwargs = kwargs
881	
882	    def send(self, mavmsg${type_mavlink_message}, force_mavlink1${type_bool_default})${type_none_ret}:
883	        """send a MAVLink message"""
884	        buf = mavmsg.pack(self, force_mavlink1=force_mavlink1)
885	        self.file.write(buf)
886	        self.seq = (self.seq + 1) % 256
887	        self.total_packets_sent += 1
888	        self.total_bytes_sent += len(buf)
889	        if self.send_callback is not None and self.send_callback_args is not None and self.send_callback_kwargs is not None:
890	            self.send_callback(mavmsg, *self.send_callback_args, **self.send_callback_kwargs)
891	
892	    def buf_len(self)${type_int_ret}:
893	        return len(self.buf) - self.buf_index
894	
895	    def bytes_needed(self)${type_int_ret}:
896	        """return number of bytes needed for next parsing stage"""
897	        ret = self.expected_length - self.buf_len()
898	
899	        if ret <= 0:
900	            return 1
901	        return ret
902	
903	    def __callbacks(self, msg${type_mavlink_message})${type_none_ret}:
904	        """this method exists only to make profiling results easier to read"""
905	        if self.callback is not None and self.callback_args is not None and self.callback_kwargs is not None:
906	            self.callback(msg, *self.callback_args, **self.callback_kwargs)
907	
908	    def parse_char(self, c${type_intseq})${type_optional_mavlink_message_ret}:
909	        """input some data bytes, possibly returning a new message"""
910	        self.buf.extend(c)
911	
912	        self.total_bytes_received += len(c)
913	
914	        m = self.__parse_char_legacy()
915	
916	        if m is not None:
917	            self.total_packets_received += 1
918	            self.__callbacks(m)
919	        else:
920	            # XXX The idea here is if we've read something and there's nothing left in
921	            # the buffer, reset it to 0 which frees the memory
922	            if self.buf_len() == 0 and self.buf_index != 0:
923	                self.buf = bytearray()
924	                self.buf_index = 0
925	
926	        return m
927	
928	    def __parse_char_legacy(self)${type_optional_mavlink_message_ret}:
929	        """input some data bytes, possibly returning a new message"""
930	        header_len = HEADER_LEN_V1
931	        if self.buf_len() >= 1 and self.buf[self.buf_index] == PROTOCOL_MARKER_V2:
932	            header_len = HEADER_LEN_V2
933	
934	        m${type_optional_mavlink_message} = None
935	        if self.buf_len() >= 1 and self.buf[self.buf_index] != PROTOCOL_MARKER_V1 and self.buf[self.buf_index] != PROTOCOL_MARKER_V2:
936	            magic = self.buf[self.buf_index]
937	            self.buf_index += 1
938	            if self.robust_parsing:
939	                m = MAVLink_bad_data(bytearray([magic]), "Bad prefix")
940	                self.expected_length = header_len + 2
941	                self.total_receive_errors += 1
942	                return m
943	            if self.have_prefix_error:
944	                return None
945	            self.have_prefix_error = True
946	            self.total_receive_errors += 1
947	            raise MAVError("invalid MAVLink prefix '%s'" % magic)
948	        self.have_prefix_error = False
949	        if self.buf_len() >= 3:
950	            sbuf = self.buf[self.buf_index : 3 + self.buf_index]
951	            (magic, self.expected_length, incompat_flags) = cast(
952	                ${type_tuple_int_int_int_cast},
953	                self.mav20_h3_unpacker.unpack(sbuf),
954	            )
955	            if magic == PROTOCOL_MARKER_V2 and (incompat_flags & MAVLINK_IFLAG_SIGNED):
956	                self.expected_length += MAVLINK_SIGNATURE_BLOCK_LEN
957	            self.expected_length += header_len + 2
958	        if self.expected_length >= (header_len + 2) and self.buf_len() >= self.expected_length:
959	            mbuf = self.buf[self.buf_index : self.buf_index + self.expected_length]
960	            self.buf_index += self.expected_length
961	            self.expected_length = header_len + 2
962	            if self.robust_parsing:
963	                try:
964	                    if magic == PROTOCOL_MARKER_V2 and (incompat_flags & ~MAVLINK_IFLAG_SIGNED) != 0:
965	                        raise MAVError("invalid incompat_flags 0x%x 0x%x %u" % (incompat_flags, magic, self.expected_length))
966	                    m = self.decode(mbuf)
967	                except MAVError as reason:
968	                    m = MAVLink_bad_data(mbuf, reason.message)
969	                    self.total_receive_errors += 1
970	            else:
971	                if magic == PROTOCOL_MARKER_V2 and (incompat_flags & ~MAVLINK_IFLAG_SIGNED) != 0:
972	                    raise MAVError("invalid incompat_flags 0x%x 0x%x %u" % (incompat_flags, magic, self.expected_length))
973	                m = self.decode(mbuf)
974	            return m
975	        return None
976	
977	    def parse_buffer(self, s${type_intseq})${type_optional_mavlink_message_list_ret}:
978	        """input some data bytes, possibly returning a list of new messages"""
979	        m = self.parse_char(s)
980	        if m is None:
981	            return None
982	        ret = [m]
983	        while True:
984	            m = self.parse_char(b"")
985	            if m is None:
986	                return ret
987	            ret.append(m)
988	
989	    def check_signature(self, msgbuf${type_bytearray}, srcSystem${type_int}, srcComponent${type_int})${type_bool_ret}:
990	        """check signature on incoming message"""
991	        assert self.signing.secret_key is not None
992	
993	        timestamp_buf = msgbuf[-12:-6]
994	        link_id = msgbuf[-13]
995	        (tlow, thigh) = cast(
996	            ${type_tuple_int_int_cast},
997	            self.mav_sign_unpacker.unpack(timestamp_buf),
998	        )
999	        timestamp = tlow + (thigh << 32)
1000	
1001	        # see if the timestamp is acceptable
1002	        stream_key = (link_id, srcSystem, srcComponent)
1003	        if stream_key in self.signing.stream_timestamps:
1004	            if timestamp <= self.signing.stream_timestamps[stream_key]:
1005	                # reject old timestamp
1006	                logger.info("old timestamp")
1007	                return False
1008	        else:
1009	            # a new stream has appeared. Accept the timestamp if it is at most
1010	            # one minute behind our current timestamp
1011	            if timestamp + 6000 * 1000 < self.signing.timestamp:
1012	                logger.info("bad new stream %s %s", timestamp / (100.0 * 1000 * 60 * 60 * 24 * 365), self.signing.timestamp / (100.0 * 1000 * 60 * 60 * 24 * 365))
1013	                return False
1014	            self.signing.stream_timestamps[stream_key] = timestamp
1015	            logger.info("new stream")
1016	
1017	        h = hashlib.new("sha256")
1018	        h.update(self.signing.secret_key)
1019	        h.update(msgbuf[:-6])
1020	        sig1 = h.digest()[:6]
1021	        sig2 = msgbuf[-6:]
1022	        if sig1 != sig2:
1023	            logger.info("sig mismatch")
1024	            return False
1025	
1026	        # the timestamp we next send with is the max of the received timestamp and
1027	        # our current timestamp
1028	        self.signing.timestamp = max(self.signing.timestamp, timestamp)
1029	        return True
1030	
1031	    def decode(self, msgbuf${type_bytearray})${type_mavlink_message_ret}:
1032	        """decode a buffer as a MAVLink message"""
1033	        # decode the header
1034	        if msgbuf[0] != PROTOCOL_MARKER_V1:
1035	            headerlen = 10
1036	            try:
1037	                magic, mlen, incompat_flags, compat_flags, seq, srcSystem, srcComponent, msgIdlow, msgIdhigh = cast(
1038	                    ${type_tuple_bytes_eight_int_cast},
1039	                    self.mav20_unpacker.unpack(msgbuf[:headerlen]),
1040	                )
1041	            except struct.error as emsg:
1042	                raise MAVError("Unable to unpack MAVLink header: %s" % emsg)
1043	            msgId = msgIdlow | (msgIdhigh << 16)
1044	            mapkey = msgId
1045	        else:
1046	            headerlen = 6
1047	            try:
1048	                magic, mlen, seq, srcSystem, srcComponent, msgId = cast(
1049	                    ${type_tuple_bytes_five_int_cast},
1050	                    self.mav10_unpacker.unpack(msgbuf[:headerlen]),
1051	                )
1052	                incompat_flags = 0
1053	                compat_flags = 0
1054	            except struct.error as emsg:
1055	                raise MAVError("Unable to unpack MAVLink header: %s" % emsg)
1056	            mapkey = msgId
1057	        if (incompat_flags & MAVLINK_IFLAG_SIGNED) != 0:
1058	            signature_len = MAVLINK_SIGNATURE_BLOCK_LEN
1059	        else:
1060	            signature_len = 0
1061	
1062	        if ord(magic) != PROTOCOL_MARKER_V1 and ord(magic) != PROTOCOL_MARKER_V2:
1063	            raise MAVError("invalid MAVLink prefix '{}'".format(hex(ord(magic))))
1064	        if mlen != len(msgbuf) - (headerlen + 2 + signature_len):
1065	            raise MAVError("invalid MAVLink message length. Got %u expected %u, msgId=%u headerlen=%u" % (len(msgbuf) - (headerlen + 2 + signature_len), mlen, msgId, headerlen))
1066	
1067	        if mapkey not in mavlink_map:
1068	            return MAVLink_unknown(msgId, msgbuf)
1069	
1070	        # decode the payload
1071	        msgtype = mavlink_map[mapkey]
1072	        order_map = msgtype.orders
1073	        len_map = msgtype.lengths
1074	        crc_extra = msgtype.crc_extra
1075	
1076	        # decode the checksum
1077	        try:
1078	            (crc,) = cast(
1079	                ${type_tuple_int_cast},
1080	                self.mav_csum_unpacker.unpack(msgbuf[-(2 + signature_len) :][:2]),
1081	            )
1082	        except struct.error as emsg:
1083	            raise MAVError("Unable to unpack MAVLink CRC: %s" % emsg)
1084	        crcbuf = msgbuf[1 : -(2 + signature_len)]
1085	        if ${crc_extra}:
1086	            # using CRC extra
1087	            crcbuf.append(crc_extra)
1088	        crc2 = x25crc(crcbuf)
1089	        if crc != crc2.crc and not MAVLINK_IGNORE_CRC:
1090	            raise MAVError("invalid MAVLink CRC in msgID %u 0x%04x should be 0x%04x" % (msgId, crc, crc2.crc))
1091	
1092	        sig_ok = False
1093	        if signature_len == MAVLINK_SIGNATURE_BLOCK_LEN:
1094	            self.signing.sig_count += 1
1095	        if self.signing.secret_key is not None:
1096	            accept_signature = False
1097	            if signature_len == MAVLINK_SIGNATURE_BLOCK_LEN:
1098	                sig_ok = self.check_signature(msgbuf, srcSystem, srcComponent)
1099	                accept_signature = sig_ok
1100	                if sig_ok:
1101	                    self.signing.goodsig_count += 1
1102	                else:
1103	                    self.signing.badsig_count += 1
1104	                if not accept_signature and self.signing.allow_unsigned_callback is not None:
1105	                    accept_signature = self.signing.allow_unsigned_callback(self, msgId)
1106	                    if accept_signature:
1107	                        self.signing.unsigned_count += 1
1108	                    else:
1109	                        self.signing.reject_count += 1
1110	            elif self.signing.allow_unsigned_callback is not None:
1111	                accept_signature = self.signing.allow_unsigned_callback(self, msgId)
1112	                if accept_signature:
1113	                    self.signing.unsigned_count += 1
1114	                else:
1115	                    self.signing.reject_count += 1
1116	            if not accept_signature:
1117	                raise MAVError("Invalid signature")
1118	
1119	        csize = msgtype.unpacker.size
1120	        mbuf = msgbuf[headerlen : -(2 + signature_len)]
1121	        if len(mbuf) < csize:
1122	            # zero pad to give right size
1123	            mbuf.extend([0] * (csize - len(mbuf)))
1124	        if len(mbuf) < csize:
1125	            raise MAVError("Bad message of type %s length %u needs %s" % (msgtype, len(mbuf), csize))
1126	        mbuf = mbuf[:csize]
1127	        try:
1128	            t = cast(
1129	                ${type_tuple_bytes_int_float_repeat_cast},
1130	                msgtype.unpacker.unpack(mbuf),
1131	            )
1132	        except struct.error as emsg:
1133	            raise MAVError("Unable to unpack MAVLink payload type=%s payloadLength=%u: %s" % (msgtype, len(mbuf), emsg))
1134	
1135	        tlist${type_mavlink_message_assign_attr_list} = list(t)
1136	        # handle sorted fields
1137	        if ${sort_fields}:
1138	            if sum(len_map) == len(len_map):
1139	                # message has no arrays in it
1140	                for i in range(0, len(tlist)):
1141	                    tlist[i] = t[order_map[i]]
1142	            else:
1143	                # message has some arrays
1144	                tlist = []
1145	                for i in range(0, len(order_map)):
1146	                    order = order_map[i]
1147	                    L = len_map[order]
1148	                    tip = sum(len_map[:order])
1149	                    field = t[tip]
1150	                    if L == 1 or isinstance(field, bytes):
1151	                        tlist.append(field)
1152	                    else:
1153	                        tlist.append(cast(${type_intseq_floatseq_cast}, list(t[tip : (tip + L)])))
1154	
1155	        # terminate any strings
1156	        for i, elem in enumerate(tlist):
1157	            if isinstance(elem, bytes):
1158	                tlist[i] = elem.rstrip(b"\\x00")
1159	
1160	        # construct the message object
1161	        try:
1162	            # Note that initializers don't follow the Liskov Substitution Principle
1163	            # therefore it can't be typechecked
1164	            m = msgtype(*tlist)  # type: ignore
1165	        except Exception as emsg:
1166	            raise MAVError("Unable to instantiate MAVLink message of type %s : %s" % (msgtype, emsg))
1167	        m._signed = sig_ok
1168	        if m._signed:
1169	            m._link_id = msgbuf[-13]
1170	        m._msgbuf = msgbuf
1171	        m._payload = msgbuf[6 : -(2 + signature_len)]
1172	        m._crc = crc
1173	        m._header = MAVLink_header(msgId, incompat_flags, compat_flags, mlen, seq, srcSystem, srcComponent)
1174	        return m
1175	''',
1176	        xml,
1177	    )
